title: CS Fresh Great World
text:
I was browsing the bread section and noticed there were no staff around, so I casually looked around the area to see if anyone might be able to assist. I spotted a lady at the meat section but wasn’t sure if she was also responsible for the bread, so I simply continued waiting, I wasn’t upset or in a hurry, just calmly looking for someone to help.
 
 Unexpectedly, the lady from the meat section walked over and said to me in a rude tone, “Don’t know how to open your mouth and ask? No one knows you need anything if you don’t ask.” I was taken aback by her attitude, but I calmly pointed to the bread I wanted and asked her to help cut it.
 
 After she finished, she repeated the same rude comment again about how if I didn’t open my mouth, no one would know, again, in a condescending tone.
 
 I want to emphasize that I really wasn’t angry or trying to find fault at all about not being attended to. But the way she spoke to me, completely unprovoked, was unnecessary and frankly, quite upsetting. Her tone and choice of words turned what was a perfectly normal situation into an unpleasant one.
 
 I hope this can be looked into, as basic courtesy and professionalism really make a difference in customer experience.
 
 Thank you.

title: CS Fresh @ Holland Shopping Centre
text:
I was shopping here a few days ago when a Tillamook Cheese Promoter asked me if I wanted to sample their cheese.
 
 I was trying to be polite by making a small talk with her, so I casually asked her if Tillamook is a new Cheese brand. But her response really shocked me.
 
 She turned her head in a dramatic slow-mo, rolled her eyes at me as she said “huhhh……?” “no…..?” “It’s been around for so long already, you didn’t hear before meh?” She said so much yet she could not tell me exactly which year was the brand founded.
 
 So she was rude and judgmental towards me when I have not heard of the brand, yet she herself as a promoter of Tillamook, don’t know when it’s founded?
 
 Isn’t the point of being a promoter, to promote and share more about the brand to customers? What’s the point of hiring one when the promoter was so judgemental yet clueless about the brand?
 
 I’m sure the reason why she’s even hired to promote at the temporary booth at CS is because the brand is unpopular and they want to make it known to CS customers, so it’s not surprising that I haven’t heard of the brand.
 
 This encounter with the female promoter really ruined my shopping experience at CS. I’d rather patronise Fairprice Finest in future.
 
 Edit: Just to add that I’ve sent a feedback to CS via email and their response felt really templated and insincere. I’m just disappointed.

But there was no indications or signs that said the machine was unable to play. He just smiles and nods in agreement?!?! Is it so hard to put the black tap on?
 
 I then went to the counter to request a refund, since there wasn't any other machine I would like to play. And the counter staff said no refunds for token.
 
 But in the first place, I wouldn't have redrawn the token if the machine showed that it was unavailable. There was no tape, and the lights and wheels were spinning.
 
 Why did your staff's negligence in doing their job cause me to need to bring home 50 tokens? Super upset hearing upon this, and your staff weren't exactly friendly either. Should i be thankful i only drawn 50 tokens out.
 
 Super bad experience in this outlet, and its not the first time! please do something about it. It is not fair for your customers too.

title: Samsung Service Centre Westgate
text:
I went to Westgate support Centre to fix my sim card tray unable to slot back in.
 
 The service personnel bring the phone to his technician, return in just 2 mins. Explain that i had broken a pin and to fix, it required a whole mother board replacement which cost $200 plus.
 
 I declined and asked if they can open the phone case to do a detailed check. The personnel assure me that it would not help and rejected my request.
 
 I went home take a closer look and discovered that the reason why the sim card tray was unable to slot in us due to a pin had jack up.
 
 I use a thin tool to press back the pin. After that I am able to slot in the sim card tray.
 
 The phone is still under warranty. The service center is unhelpful and recommend an expensive solution. I am totally disgusted.

text: I would come back to stay here again. Great location, easy to access via MRT from airport or other main stations. Close to local food spots like chinatown market or maxwell food centre. title: Al Capone’s
text:
I would give ZERO stars if I could. Went there on Friday evening, ordered 2 Stout, 1 Heineken and 1 Truffle Fries- and th ordeal started

 2. Stout came after a few minutes but the Heineken didn't. Literally and I repeat without exaggerating, it must have taken at least 10-15 mins for the 3rd Beer that's on tap to come. I mean really?? How long does it take to pour a glass from a tap. It was clear that the service was really disappointing and it almost felt like some other customers were being given priority.
 3. The fries never came btw. 30-45 mins of sitting there, no one said anything, Enquired and was told 'oh there's only one chef today. Could have given a heads-up before taking the order or at least told us while we were waiting forever just to have fries along with Beer.

title: CS Fresh Great World
text:
I’d like to raise a concern about a very rude staff member at your store, his behavior has been consistently unprofessional, and I strongly urge CS Fresh to review this issue.
 
 A few weeks ago, someone had spilled a drink on the floor. As I was pushing a trolley and unknowingly approached the area, this staff member stood nearby and abruptly shouted “Oi!” before pointing at the spill. His expression was extremely hostile!
 almost as if to say, “Are you blind?” It was unnecessarily aggressive and humiliating.
 
 On another occasion, I witnessed him act rudely toward a couple browsing at the bakery section. He arrived with multiple carts and attempted to push through a narrow space without saying “Excuse me” or asking politely. Instead, he glared at the couple with an exaggerated, wide-eyed stare, silently pressuring them to move. Startled, they quickly stepped aside. It was uncomfortable to witness.
 
 Later, when I went to pay for my items, I told the cashier that I’d return shortly to grab a few more packs of blueberries. I placed my cart aside temporarily. This same staff member then ordered me to push my cart over and return to the bakery area, even though I had already informed the cashier of my plan. It felt controlling and unnecessary.
 
 Fortunately, another staff member noticed and kindly offered to help move my cart. His helpful attitude stood in stark contrast to the rude behavior I’ve described.
 
 Staff training and professionalism are essential to the shopping experience. Customers should never feel intimidated or disrespected. I sincerely hope CS Fresh takes this feedback seriously and addresses this individual’s behavior appropriately.

I am also grateful to Mr JY who further educated me on the computer information. Both are great people. Finally I bought a laptop from them.

title: Cosmo Massage & Reflexology (Precious Foot) - Massage | Tui na | Foot Massage | Gua Sha - Toa Payoh
text: I’ve been coming here for over 4 years and it’s always a great experience. Raini is especially amazing — his foot massages are precise, effective, and super relaxing. The place is clean, calm, and professional, with no hard sell, which I really appreciate. Highly recommend!

title: Blind Massage Services
text:
I’ve been coming to Blind Massage Services a few times now based on recommendations from friends, and it’s quickly become one of my go-to spots. Although the therapists may lack sight, they more than make up for it with their incredible skill, intuition, and ability to identify all my problem areas without me even having to say a word.
 
 I especially love their foot massages — truly some of the best I’ve had! What makes the experience even better is the warm, personal touch. They greet you by name when you arrive, remembering the day’s appointments by memory alone, and check in with you during the massage to make sure everything’s comfortable. I also appreciate the little gesture of offering warm water after each session.

title: Great Shelford Tree
text: I’ve been hearing this shelford tree for quite awhile now and finally I get to see it today! Really impressive!

title: Spa Bonito
text:
I’ve been looking for Monica for my massage appointment ever since I followed her over from another spa. Massage given by her has always been awesome.
 She’s super professional, easy to chat with, and knows exactly how much pressure to apply.
 Monica’s bubbly personality and sunny vibe are something you will appreciate at the end of a tired working day.
 Every visit leaves me feeling refreshed and renewed. I highly recommend Monica to anyone in search of a top-tier massage therapist.

title: Kang Zu Tang Therapy 康足堂
text:
I’ve been recommended to Helen姊 for treatment as she has been known to treat a number of conditions successfully (including eczema, female fertility, adult and babies with body or movement anomalies etc.)
 
 Visited Helen姊 since May for my condition - raised cancer markers. From end of 2023 to early 2024, I’ve was following up with a specialist for regular blood test but the level kept increasing exponentially, but there were no significant findings via CT scans.
 
 After going for treatments from May till August, the blood test showed a significant 30% drop in the levels. Not only does her treatment target the specific issue, but she also helps to nurse and tune the body back to good health. Truly grateful to have met Helen姊 🙏🏻

title: MY Clinic
text: I’ve been to many skincare clinics, but this one stands out! The treatments are effective, and they use the latest technology. My skin feels refreshed and rejuvenated after each visit. Patricia @Austin Jb best beautifician

title: Advantage Medical Clinic, Bukit Timah (Guthrie House) | GP Clinic, Medical Centre, XRay, Health Screening
text:
I’ve been trying to look around for ear syringing and I’m so thankful that this clinic does it. Weekends get busy, weekdays are still ok!
 
 Dr Brendan Yap was patient and did a good job at flushing out my stubborn ear wax.
 
 Definitely recommend this place.

title: TOOTH ANGELS Coronation Arcade
text:
I’ve been with Dr April since 2016 when they were not even at this current location. Dr April and team has always provided top tier professionalism - from clearly explaining dental plans (I started with metal braces) to customer service towards anything I need. For the former, my braces journey took 5 years and I was always well informed (plus my consent explicitly sought) of the assessments and plans of what we’re doing and why we’re doing that. And for the latter, there were already a few “emergencies” where I either broke a bracket or my retainers and they would make a few work arounds to accommodate my schedule as best as they can.
 
 It’s been a pleasure to be a patient at this clinic and I foresee that I will stick with them for all my dental needs for the foreseeable future :)

title: Little Big Coffee Roasters
text: I’ve gone here twice so far and haven’t been disappointed. Love their white coffee.

title: Eng Seng Motor
text:
I’ve make a wise choice to send my car to Eng Seng Motor for I carelessly scratched & hit a kerb. I’m impressed how fast & fuss free to arrange my car to them.
 
 The make over was super as I cannot find a flaw for the corner of my light that I had damaged so badly from the hit & the spray job was great, I cannot tell a flaw as the touched up colour blended so well with my car
 
 I highly recommend Alvin service whom he’s accommodative & easy to drop off & collect my car for service & he promised & delivered what we had discussed & completed ahead of time.
 
 I will surely recommend friends to give them a try & send their precious car & give a top 10 service to this workshop 👍

title: Holland Village Market & Food Centre
text:
If I can give no star, I will. Ordered medium size, thinking the seller would put in more effort to cook. But the theory did not working.
 
 I know the difference between 'wok hei' and 'badly charred / burnt'. This was the latter.
 
 The carrot cake smells and tastes like it was scrapped from a wok that had very badly burnt food. The dark sauce was watery, which I think could be due to sub-par condiment being used.
 
 Thank you, no more second time!
 
 All the best from a hardcore diner who grew up having fried carrot cake as part of the meals in his life.
 
 No wonder there is no queue even during peak lunch hour.

title: AutoSprint
text:
If i could give 6 stars, i would.
 
 These guys truly live up to the Company's name. Not only was the process smooth and AUTOmated, they got the OBU installation done in less than 2 hours, almost like they were SPRINTing.
 
 Truly appreciated them answering the 101 questions i had and accomodating my fussy-ness. Whatsapp is manned promptly and you get replies as soon as you are dont taking a breath after typing. Staff are extremely helpful and courteous.
 
 If I can, i will come here to install a 100 more OBUs just to enjoy the good service. hahahahah

title: Squad Workshop
text:
If I could, I’d give 10 Stars to Royston, Meryl and their awesome team of mechanics David and Ah Kai!
 
 Simply my Go To for anything car related especially VAG as that’s Royston’s specialty. However that doesn’t mean they can’t handle Non VAG cars. They have worked on my Honda, my BMW and on my other friends Toyota, Lexus and many more! They have solved problems even on a Rolls Royce Ghost that other supposed workshops thought they could. And why? This boils down to EFFORT, KNOWLEDGE and COMMITMENT that is deeply rooted into this power team. The commitment that is derived from the NEVER SAY DIE spirit of theirs is something I deeply respect 🫡
 
 Those who know me know I don’t trust workshops easily but Squad is the 1 of ONLY 2 Workshops I patronise whom I can entrust my car to and simply go for a holiday even and know that the car is in trustable good hands.
 
 3 Cheers for this wonderful hardworking and knowledgeable team, who are always me and my cars their best!!

title: Samsung Service Centre Westgate
text:
If it were possible to give zero stars, I would.
 I recently spoke with a technician named King, and unfortunately, the experience was extremely disappointing. The technician was unhelpful and provided explanations that I found to be unreasonable and unsatisfactory regarding why my phone could not be repaired. I expected better service from a company like Samsung, and I believe it would benefit from having more competent and customer-focused technicians.

title: North Bridge Road Market & Food Centre
text: If you are looking for a clean and pleasant place to have a meal this is the place. Look out for Heng Heng Wanton Noodle. The vendor is friendly and cooks great wanton noodles, served with a generous portion of vegetables. Tasty and healthy. A wholesome meal!

title: Spa Bonito
text: If you are looking for a strong, skillfull masseuse, you can look for Lulu. Despite her petite size, she got strength and skill. She knows where to find my painful points and despite my large frame, she was able to consistently provide the strong strength throughout the 90 minute session. I'd recommend Lulu for those who needs strong and good massage.

title: The Clinic Group @ Business City
text: If you are sick and working in the area, do not come to this clinic. They allow student check up to enter the consultation room first. Those who reached later than me get to go into consultation room earlier than me. I sat for 30mins with fever cough n flu, but unable to get to consult the doctor. It is not even crowded. When asked, they say cos the students got appointments. If this is the case, you should not do walk in patients, just do appointments. Terrible clinic and i have to cancel my registration after waiting for 45mins. Imaginr a sick man got to cancel clinic registration and find another clinic to seek consultation, not because this clinic is very crowded, but because they simply do not bother much about walk in patient.

title: Blind Massage Services
text:
If you like acupressure/ deep tissue/ tuina massage, make sure you come to this place. I had a full back (40mins) & foot reflex (60mins) for $70, the most affordable & quality massage I ever had locally. The place is simple, no frill, the focus is on the massage itself not the fancy stuff.
 The masseur is professional, experienced and friendly, the pressure was perfect and all my kinks and knots smoothed out.
 The place is owned and operated by the visually impaired, their professionalism and skill easily out rival any other establishment, IMO.
 If you care for a chat, the team is happy to share their knowledge and experience.
 To me it is not only a much needed massage, it is also a life lesson in respecting others’ space and sense of self.
 If you chance upon a person with limitations, ask “how can I help?” instead of making assumptions.
 
 Definitely recommend to my family & friends!

title: Little Big Coffee Roasters
text:
If you like coffee, this is one of the place to check out!
 Environment is warm, not too bright. Service is good as well.
 
 Highly recommended!

title: Riverview Auto Services Pte Ltd
text:
If you’re looking for a repair shop, look no further. I’m quite particular when it comes to my personal car. Used to have an 1993 E36 and was always quoted sky high prices. Look for Vincent (Boss) or Kanash (BMW expert) and they will always explain clearly to you and will only repair what’s needed unlike many other ws out there who will tell you to change this change that and charge you unreasonable prices.
 
 Recently had changed to a CLA and still, i’ve absolute trust in riverview auto, Xiao Yang has been maintaining my car ever since and i’ve no issues at all!
 
 Thumbs up to Vincent and team!
 I guess for the rest of my driving life, i’ll only choose riverview auto!

title: Baden Restaurant & Pub
text:
If you’re looking for an authentic slice of Germany right in the heart of Holland Village, Baden Restaurant & Pub is the place to be! The moment you step in, you’re greeted with warm, rustic charm and a lively, welcoming atmosphere that makes you feel right at home.
 
 The food is absolutely top-notch – hearty, flavorful, and made with love. The pork knuckle is hands down one of the best in Singapore: crispy on the outside, tender on the inside, and served with rich, savory gravy. Pair it with their signature sausages and a cold German beer, and you’ve got the perfect meal.
 
 The staff are friendly, attentive, and genuinely passionate about what they do. Service is prompt even during peak hours, and they’re always happy to offer recommendations if you’re unsure what to try.
 
 Whether you’re here for a relaxed dinner, a round of beers with friends, or just to soak in the vibes, Baden never disappoints. It’s a rare gem that keeps you coming back for more!
 
 Highly recommend – 5 stars all the way!

title: HaveFun Karaoke (Suntec City)
text: If you're a cosplayer or anime fan, you NEED to check out HaveFun Suntec. The room vibe is perfect for photos, and they even had tons of J-pop and anisong options.

title: Coffee Tea Library
text:
If you're into tea — like really into tea — you’ve got to check out Coffee Tea Library. This place is seriously a haven for anyone who enjoys a good cup of something warm and calming. They’ve got a crazy wide selection of tea leaves from all over, and it’s not just the basic stuff. Think oolongs, rare white teas, deep earthy pu-erhs, and everything in between.
 
 The vibe here is super chill — kind of like a cozy book café meets a modern tea shop. There are books everywhere, comfy seating, and it’s quiet enough to read, work, or just zone out with your drink.
 
 What I loved most was how helpful the staff were. I wasn’t sure what to try, but they actually asked what kind of flavors I like and suggested a couple options I ended up loving. They do serve coffee too (which is pretty solid), and have a few snacks and pastries if you’re hungry, but honestly, the tea is what makes this place shine.
 
 Definitely worth a visit if you’re looking for a relaxed spot to sip and chill — or if you’re just bored of the usual café scene.

title: Chupitos
text:
If you're looking for a place that promises you a indoor seat, only to give your seat away after an hour — look no further! This bar truly excels at setting expetation.
 
 The manager? (The Black Guy) An absolute gem — if you're into being spoken to with attitude and zero professionalism. Rude, dismissive, and clearly has no idea how to manage a team or a guest list.
 
 Customer service? Nonexistent. Accountability? Also missing. Hospitality? Definitely not in their vocabulary.
 
 Save yourself the headache. There are plenty of other bars in Clark Quay that know how to treat people with basic respect.

title: Oldies karaoke lounge
text:
If you're looking for a spot where the good times never stop, this karaoke pub has been the heartbeat of my weekends for many years.
 
 It’s not just a bar or a venue — it’s a gathering spot where you can truly be yourself and let loose. If you're looking for a place to create memories with friends (or even strangers who quickly become friends), this karaoke pub is the place to be.

Rude security uncles and staff playing games with the drink prices and your change round out the reasons why you should just save your $$$ and go to Batam or Bangkok instead. RIP the good ol’ days…

title: Central Square Canteen
text:
It is a smaller canteen, compared to Frontier, Deck, or Technoedge. It has several stalls — Thai, Mala, Mixed Vegetable Rice, Ban Mian/Fish Soup, and Indian (Vegetarian).
 
 For the Thai food:
 1. The green curry chicken is good, but quite spicy. The chicken slices are quite plenty.
 2. The pandan chicken is also good -- it is well-marinated and juicy.
 
 For the Ban Mian/Fish soup stall:
 1. The double fish soup is good. You can opt for milk to be put in as well. 2. The dumplings are also good. It is filled with a mixture of chives and pork and is juicy.
 3. The tomato egg noodle is good too. It is like ban mian, except that the soup base is sweet and slightly tangy.
 
 For the La Mian/Hotplate stall, they have beef noodle. The beef slices are tender, but maybe, the spicy option would be better, as the non-spicy option made the soup tasted salty.
 
 For the Waffles stall, they have the waffle with ice cream. The waffle itself is crispy. The ice cream flavors are also quite good -- I particularly liked the cookies and cream and the mango.

title: CS Fresh Great World
text:
It was my first time visiting this Cold Storage outlet to buy fresh fish. I selected a larger piece and asked the service staff to help cut it into smaller portions and pack them into separate bags, so I could cook them on different days.
 
 However, after the staff finished cutting the fish, I noticed he did not wear gloves during the entire process. Even more concerning, he handled the raw fish with bare hands and didn’t wash his hands before placing the pieces into the plastic bags. Later, when he handled another clean bag for storing other raw meat, he still didn’t wash his hands beforehand.
 
 This is a serious hygiene issue that could lead to cross-contamination and increase the risk of foodborne illness or even something more severe. It was extremely upsetting and unacceptable to witness such unsafe food handling practices.
 
 I sincerely hope the management takes this matter seriously and ensures all staff are properly trained before assigning them to such important roles. No customer should have to worry about food poisoning due to poor hygiene standards.

title: Round 1 Karaoke Pub

title: Phuture
text:
It's a scam... The ushers at the entrance are very arrogant, talk to you as if they want to beat you up!
 
 I bought a voucher on Grab and the terms and condition only stated that the voucher should be redeemed on either Wednesday, Friday or Saturday. I went on a Saturday night, and showed them that I was there to redeem my voucher. The staff at the entrance told me I couldn’t use it because they had a special guest that night and wanted to 'avoid losses.'
 
 When I asked which terms and conditions could prevent me from entering because of the presence of special guests, they told me it's their decision now and they would inform Grab partnership team next time. It becomes my own problem and I should deal with Grab myself instead!
 
 Interestingly, the staff then admitted that the voucher is a clickbait as they don't want the customer to redeem the voucher, even though the voucher has stated that it should be redeemed within the specified day and period.
 
 Does this imply that Zouk being a big and trusted corporation are playing click bait to cheat the customers? This is not only unprofessional but also completely disregards the rights of your customers!
 
 When I asked to record their statement to raise dispute against Grab, one of the staff touched my phone and raised her tone towards me. This is completely unacceptable. First, did you have permission to touch my personal property? Second, how can you not take responsibility for what you've said, yet still represent Zouk?
 
 I asked for their manager's email and emailed them the day after. But even after 4 days, there's no reply at all. So GO AT YOUR OWN RISK!

title: b88 hostel
text:
I've stayed at the b88 for 2 weeks somewhere around November '12. Was very pleasantly surprised at the quality of the digs and the services that the staff provide. The rooms are clean, well ventilated and the beds and mattresses comfortable. For me, the most important aspect were the toilets and bathrooms - these were always kept spic and span.
 The staff are all young, locals, mostly studying at colleges, and consequently really know their way around town - they're really helpful and super friendly too. If you ever have a day where you don't have much to do, relax in their common area - its the ultimate way to meet new people and make some awesome friends! All in all, a really good place to stay.
 This is also one of the very few places in Singapore that i know of that doesn't burn through one's holiday money simply on accommodation costs. Very reasonably priced, it is for the budget conscious (which is, i think 90% of all travelers). Singapore is no longer a rich man's holiday destination. Thank you b88! :)

title: Royal Albatross - Luxury Tall Ship
text:
Just to feedback that we attended the dinner cruise on 24/8 Night and had a very wonderful experience on the Royal Albatross, and it was our first time attending.
 
 However, there is 1 issue we need to highlight.
 
 We sat next to the bar counter, on the first table when guests first enter and walk up the steps.
 Everything was perfect except when eating the cake halfway, my wife bit on a staple bullet which she managed to extract from her mouth.
 
 Thankfully, there was no injury or bleeding and we highlighted it to the waiter (Malay gentleman) who was very apologetic, immediately removed the cake and offered us a mocktail each FOC.
 We had a lovely evening and do not want one negative issue to mar the whole experience.
 Hence its unfortunate that this happened and hope you can investigate or highlight this with your birthday cake vendor to ensure that it doesnt happen again (I'm sure they can figure out where the staple bullet originated from).
 
 Unfortunately, we were too shocked and forgot to take a photo, but just writing a note here for the record.
 Post-dinner, i wrote an email to followup and close off this matter but did not receive a reply.
 Hope it has been investigated and resolved. Ideally, i would have liked a refund on the cake alone too. It doesnt seem right to have paid for a cake with a staple bullet and which was thrown away half eaten.

So yesterday 12/8/2023 we went down to club slim again to claim out left over bottle (Chivas 18) sadly the staff and managers there come back to us that our bottle had been redeem on the 8/8/2023 which we never went down on that day.
 
 The managers was telling me that so sadly that your name and phone number of the bottle had been redeemed. At the end of the day they just came back to me that our system showed your name had redeemed and did not do any further service recovery!
 
 The other sad things about it was yesterday we open beer tower and the promo is 2+1 they are conflict also. title: ValueMax Pawnshop & Jewellery (People's Park Centre Branch)
text:
Located in an older mall, People's Park Centre, this location of the ValueMax chain had good service and a good inventory for their size.
 
 Buys and sells gold jewelry by the gram, with a percentage cut below or above the price of gold, respectively. Combination of new and secondhand pieces available. Secondhand pieces don't have VAT tax (7%) or a workmanship fee (~7-8?%), new pieces do.
 
 They prefer cash, atm card, or NETS. They'll charge 3% for a CC, including foreign (VISA, MC) debit card. There is some wiggle room; in my purchase I couldn't withdraw enough cash due to a foreign atm limit and didn't want to pay the cc surcharge. I was going to come back the next day, but they got manager override to waive the cc fee.

Short walk to Boat Quay & Clark Quay, China Town & Centre Business District.Checked in on a Sunday evening. It was very quiet. Staff informed me that the pub upstairs doesn't operate on Sundays. This Capsule/Pod Hostel is newly opened wef Jan 2024. Hence, the aircons are very powerful, extremely clean and comfortable beddings, clean bathrooms. Except you need to go out of the main entrance to use the toilets and hv to key in a separate set password to enter the toilets. There is a big fridge next to the entrance for guests to use. Free coffee, tea, milo and water at the pantry. Area is safe, although there is a pub upstairs. ADD ON ： Extended my stay for another 2 nights, and realised that once after 12 midnight there is less noise from pub as live band stops. You can hear fade music at Room B ( the 16 female pods) but I solved it by listening to music on my earpiece and I usually sleep at 1 am hence it doesnt affect me as much. I think it will be quieter at Room A ( mixed pods) as it is further away. I paid around $38 per night and stayed at a corner lower deck pod. It is definitely value for money if you are looking at a clean capsule hotel at a good location. Honestly, throughout the 3 nights, I slept well, there wasn't any noise from the other pods as this place is relatively new hence it is not fully occupied thus not many people walking in and out.

title: Bluewaters Pods 11 North Canal Road
text:
Location is perfect. Very near many tourists spots like Chinatown, little India, Bugis, Merlion and Boat quay. Very near the MRT station that has 2 intersecting lines.
 
 Bed itself was extremely clean, and room was spacious even though it's a bunk bed.
 
 The room was vacuumed daily too.
 
 The only challenge was the noise and bathroom.
 There were only 3 showers and toilets was outside the hotel's main door.
 Since area is full of bars, the noise at night lasts until 2 am.
 
 Other than that, check in and out are a breeze. Definitely recommend this place.

title: Atelier Lounge & Bar
text:
Love the vibes here. Atelier Lounge & Bar – Where Sophistication Meets Soul in the Heart of Singapore
 
 Tucked within the stylish Pullman Singapore, Atelier Lounge & Bar is a hidden gem that blends artful ambiance with elevated drinking and dining. From plush seating to mood-lit interiors, every detail invites you to unwind — whether you’re here for a laid-back afternoon tea or a spirited evening rendezvous.
 
 The menu? Refined yet approachable. Think artisanal cocktails crafted with flair, premium wines, and curated spirits alongside thoughtful bites and sharing platters. Their mixologists don’t just serve drinks — they tell stories through every glass, whether you’re sipping a bold negroni or a fragrant floral gin creation.
 
 Whether you’re networking, decompressing, or simply indulging, Atelier Lounge & Bar delivers that sweet spot of calm and class. It’s not just a bar — it’s a conversation starter, a retreat, a mood.
 
 📍 Pullman Singapore Hill Street
 ⏰ Perfect for after-work drinks, elegant catch-ups, or quiet solo moments

title: ValueMax Pawnshop & Jewellery Shop (Tekka Centre Branch)
text:
Me and my fiancee recently went there on 11/7/2022. Miss Sally was very friendly and showed great customer service and explained with clarity.
 Variety is less, 916 gold price much higher than market price. But there's no MC nor GST charges. Therefore when calculate with other jewelry shops, its still cheaper and you get to save more.
 There's an option to pay via 3 month installment with no interest fee..
 If more than 3 month then there's 0.7% interest added (which is reasonable).
 Can walk in to pay any date within the month, flexible.
 
 Good value for the deal.
 👍👍👍👍👍

Mei Ling Food Center is one of the most underrated Hawkers Centers in Singapore in terms of the food and pricing.
 
 Parking is a little complex due to the tightness of the multi-storey carpark, and the tables can be dirty sometimes, but the dishes served here definitely compensate for it with the amount/quality of food compared to the price.
 
 Personal recommendations are the chicken rice and the fruit juice stalls.

title: MEIDI-YA Supermarket Great World

 The store is well-stocked, and items are clearly labeled, making shopping easy. Also a large selection for Japanese alcoholic drinks.
 
 There’s also a wide selection of hot cooked food and bento available, perfect for a quick meal or takeaway.

title: My Car Auto Workshop Singapore | Carworkshop.com.sg
text: My car Malfunction Warning Indicator Light started blinking on Valentine's Day, Wednesday, (5th Day of the Lunar New Year). Did some research on the internet and found some workshops with positive reviews. However, Mincent Car Workshop Singapore was the only workshop with 5 Stars rating and all positive reviews. Tried calling them and other's positive reviews workshop on Thursday, however they were closed. Finally contacted Mincent on Friday and spoke with the boss's Junyang that I will dropped by his workshop in the afternoon after 2pm. My car was vibrating violently both when idling and driving, checked my car's manual and it could be my Electronic Control Unit (ECU) issues. Asked him if my car should be tow to his workshop or I am still able to drive there. He advised driving slowly to the workshop and if there are any problems, I can contact him immediately. Managed to reached his workshop at about 3.30pm. As it is still CNY's holidays, his workshop has only 1 mechanic, otherwise he would have 3 to 4 mechanics. His partner in business spoke to me when I arrived there, and directly me to Junyang. Both him and his partner are customer's oriented persons and very sociable. They will interact with customers and explain clearly the problems with their cars and what needed to be done and the cost of the repairs before proceeding with the repairs. They price is very reasonable. As they do not store a lot of spare parts in their small workshop, they have to ordered from their regular suppliers. Despite that, they are able to diagnosed my car's problems within 30 minutes (4pm). Luckily the problems were my spark plugs and ignition coils, and not my ECU. I agreed on the cost of the repairs and I drove my car home at 5 plus, despite there were many customers at his workshop. His mechanic is very skilled, knowledgeable and friendly as well. Thank you Junyang and his team at Mincent! I will return there if I need to do regular maintenances and other car services in the future! I will definitely recommend Mincent to my friends and colleagues!

text:

The music was absolutely on point — deep, groovy, and so well-curated. If you're into quality electronic / techno / house music, this place delivers. The vibe is super cool, energetic but not chaotic, and everyone there just gets it.
 
 Bonus point: met so many fun people here — apparently a lot of folks who didn’t get into Rabbit Hole (the new viral gay club) end up here, so... yes, the eye candy is real 😆 but even beyond that, the crowd was fun, respectful, and full of good energy.
 
 Also, shoutout to the fact that they have an OUTDOOR SMOKING AREA — yes!!! You can actually step out, get some air, and still be part of the vibe. It's little things like this that make a night out feel just right.
 
 All in all — music, crowd, atmosphere, energy — everything was perfect. I’m in love with this place. See you again soon, Tuff Club!!!

title: Luss Restaurant & Bar
text:
My partner and I came here for Valentine's yesterday! We came down right after school, and even though I was carrying a bulky bag with my wrestling shoes dangling on the side, they welcomed us without complaint. From the steps up to the last meal, the food, service and atmosphere were excellent.
 
 We were told that there was a bustling crowd right before we came, so 9pm seems to be the quietest time, in case anyone has the same idea for a date!
 
 The food: We ordered the Pasta, Mala, Pork Belly Skewers, Crab Meat and Buns, two Mocktails, and the Cheese Platter. Each one was as good as the next, and the prices were very reasonably priced for the amazing quality.
 
 The place: The restaurant is situated around a quiet, off the road curb, with stairs leading up to it. It is nested within beautiful nature, with air-conditioned indoor seating, and outdoor seating as well. The restaurant's manager, I believe, was extremely accommodating, and we spoke for a bit. She also adjusted the air-condition for us when we felt chilly.
 
 Before we left, she gave us two roses, which are very appreciated =)
 
 Overall, the whole experience was just really, really pleasant. This will be our new date night spot, and honestly we wanted to gatekeep this...but we also want this place to thrive, so there you go! Visit this place, you will not regret it.
 
 Side note: As two young University students, we aren't normally paid much attention to at restaurants, which is all well and good since I'm happy having our alone time, but it is a really appreciated and welcoming gesture from the waiters and manager to speak to us. A refreshing experience indeed!

title: Bluewaters Pods 11 North Canal Road
text:
My recent stay here booked through Agoda was a series of unacceptable shortcomings. Upon arrival at midnight, the complete lack of signage for the establishment made finding it an exasperating experience. Exhausted from travel, I finally located the place with the assistance of a helpful stranger – on the top floor of a building where even other tenants seemed unaware of its existence.
 
 The frustration continued at the check-in. There was no staffed front desk, and the information provided by the staff regarding check-in details was incomplete and ultimately unusable. Two other guests faced similar issues, struggling with incorrect access codes. Thankfully, another guest assisted us in deciphering the unclear instructions, a process that consumed a frustrating thirty minutes. Despite repeated attempts to reach staff through the Agoda app, no assistance was provided.
 
 The deficiencies continued within the capsule room itself. The extreme lack of ventilation and absence of at least a small fan inside the capsule made for an uncomfortably hot environment. Even with the curtain partially open for a semblance of air circulation, the temperature remained stifling. As if the physical discomfort wasn't enough, the night was plagued by excessive noise. Loud karaoke music from a nearby bar echoed through the walls throughout the early hours, hindering sleep. Furthermore, the capsule design offered minimal soundproofing, allowing even minor noises from other guests to easily disrupt the tranquility of the room.
 
 The final indignity came in the form of the shared bathroom. Located outside the hotel itself, it was a dirty and inconvenient communal facility. This unsanitary situation was the final straw. The next morning, I promptly checked out, deeply dissatisfied with the entire experience. This stay fell far short of even the most basic hospitality standards. If you prioritize comfort and a well-maintained environment, I strongly recommend avoiding this accommodation entirely.

title: Accord Auto Services Pte Ltd
text:
MY THOUGHTS ON ACCORD AUTO SERVICES @ 09 JUN 2025
 
 I visited Accord Auto Services (Accord) at its 1009 Bukit Merah Lane workshop Monday, 02 June 2025 before my travel on Sat, 07 June 2025 and I like to share my good impressions on the competence and professionalism of the team especially, Gilbert and Ah Hao.
 
 I observed that Accord has the precise BMW diagnostic tools and professional expertise to diagnose and systematically assess “the morning cold start idling” issue which I have been experiencing for a few months.
 
 From checks and research thus far, I understand that the cold start issue (apparently common to many older BMW cars) could be caused by (1) some faulty ECU sensors; or/and (2) clogged fuel injector/sin cylinders; and/or (3) overnight fuel injectors’ bleeding…
 
 I must say that I truly appreciate the Accord service team’s professional diligence and comprehensive cum thorough diagnosis of the car’s engine and ECU sensors. The diagnostic process took about two odd hours and the Accord team managed to diagnose that the Nitrogen Oxide or NOx sensor [which was replaced in July 2023 by another workshop but unsure if that NOx sensor replaced then had been correctly coded] is faulty and unwittingly send erroneous signals to the ECU and causing the morning cold start and (unfortunate cum annoying) rough idling issue …
 
 On the very next day, Tue, 03 Jun 2025, the Accord team promptly texted the quote and estimated downtime to replace the NOx sensor. As I am travelling now, I look forward to arranging the NOx sensor replacement with Accord when I return from my travel in late June 2025.
 
 I shall also try to update/ cross-share and cross-learn further for those who have same or other engine issues concerning their BMW cars.

title: Great Shelford Tree
text:
Nestled in the cozy cul-de-sac on Shelford Road, the Great Shelford Tree is more than just a solitary tree; it’s an enchanting landmark and a celebrated tourist attraction that holds the power to transform your perspective and inspire profound reflection. This hidden gem, while seemingly simple, is a breathtaking reminder of nature’s beauty and resilience, standing tall against the backdrop of suburban life.
 
 As you approach, the ambiance shifts. The gentle rustling of leaves and the occasional chirp of birds create a serene soundtrack that invites you to pause and breathe deeply. The tree, with its sprawling branches and lush green canopy, forms a natural cathedral, beckoning visitors to experience its tranquility. I vividly remember my first visit on a sunny afternoon; the light filtered through the leaves, casting intricate patterns on the ground, making it feel almost magical.
 
 What truly sets the Great Shelford Tree apart is its history. Local lore suggests that this tree has stood for over a century, witnessing the ebb and flow of life around it. Generations of families have gathered beneath its branches for picnics, storytelling, and even proposals. I spoke to a local elder who fondly recounted how, as a child, he would climb its sturdy limbs, feeling like a king surveying his kingdom. It’s clear this tree has served as a silent witness to countless life events, each one adding to its mystique.
 
 Visitors often come not just for the beauty, but for the personal connections they forge with this magnificent tree. I’ve seen people leave behind tokens—a painted rock, a love note, or a small memento—each representing a moment of joy or a wish for the future. On my second visit, I joined a group of artists for a plein air painting session. The atmosphere was electric, filled with laughter and creativity as we each attempted to capture the tree’s essence. As I painted, I felt a connection to those who had come before me, each brushstroke a tribute to the tree’s enduring legacy.
 
 The Great Shelford Tree also serves as a hub for the community. Throughout the year, various events take place around this majestic tree—seasonal festivals, quaint gatherings, and meditation sessions. The camaraderie is palpable as friends connect over their love for this natural wonder.
 
 One of the most poignant aspects of the Great Shelford Tree is its capacity for reflection. Standing beneath its vast canopy, I often contemplate my life journey. In a world that feels overwhelming, this tree offers grounding and peace. It has become a personal sanctuary where I can escape the hustle and bustle of daily life.
 
 For those seeking inspiration, solace, or a simple moment of connection with nature, the Great Shelford Tree is an essential stop. It’s not just a tourist attraction; it’s a life-changing experience that encourages you to slow down, appreciate the beauty around you, and forge connections—with both nature and those around you.
 
 If you find yourself in the vicinity, I urge you to pay a visit. Bring a journal, a sketchbook, or simply your thoughts. You may leave with a renewed sense of purpose or just a smile, knowing you’ve encountered something truly special. The Great Shelford Tree isn’t just a tree; it’s a monument to life itself, waiting to share its wisdom with anyone willing to listen.

 Cons:

 • Rooms are small and lack windows

 • No breakfast provided, yet still on the pricey side
 
 Overall:
 I had a decent stay and, despite some downsides, would definitely consider returning.

title: My Car Auto Workshop Singapore | Carworkshop.com.sg
text:
Not someone who will stick to a workshop unless they have earned my trust, or just because a friend recommended. But Mincent Car Workshop has already won me over with my previous visits.
 
 Although the team is pretty new, and the mechanics are young. Their expertise is far beyond their age. Ah Kuan has a very high standard of work, and is able to find the root cause of issues very easily. When an engine rebuild is done, he does a stand-by bed standard of placing parts so that nothing is missed out. The other 2 mechanics are also attentive to details, and will clarify any issues you report.
 
 Being my 4th visit so far, they have saved me quite alot of money by finding out the actual real root cause, instead of just making you replace everything like some workshops do....
 
 Solutions provided are well thought out and they are linked up with the Malaysia branches so parts can be easily sourced even for old cars. Reasonable pricing, service is unrivalled
 
 Do give them a try!

On 30 Dec 2024 about 1030pm, my son prepared his own slurpee he being a child did not see the signs not to use the machine when the red light button is on. Hence, the drink was watery.
 
 I clarified with the male cashier if there’s anything wrong and he asked if it the red light was on. Realizing that, I asked if my child could get a new cup but he replied that the waterly cup is still chargeable, citing losses as a reason
 
 He did ask if my son ok with the waterly drink and he said ok. Sensing my frustration about the drink not being in perfect condition, he offered to pour half a cup away and allowed me to refill the other half.
 
 I wish he could have just provided a better service by replacing the whole cup, instead of half cup. The whole experience will be different.

title: Spacepod
text: One of the early capsule hotels in Singapore. It's located in Kallang, quite close to the MRT. There are a few dining options nearby, but not too many. It includes a standard self-service free breakfast with coffee/tea and bread with various jams. The capsules are fairly spacious, even though they're in a small room. The air conditioning is cold, and the Wi-Fi is fast. Recommended for those who just need a place to sleep for work or business.

title: Palace Therapy Spa Massage
text:
One of, if not the WORST massages I've had. Spent $66 for an hour of back massage and I specifically asked for more pressure, but the masseuse immediately refused, saying, "Let's not, I don't want to injure you." Instead of an actual massage, I was left with what felt like a light caress over my entire body—completely ineffective and not at all what I paid for.
 
 To make things worse, she even asked me which areas hurt the most, and I clearly mentioned my neck and back. Yet, she completely ignored my request and barely focused on those areas at all. What was the point of asking if she wasn’t going to listen?
 
 The most disturbing part was that her touch felt unprofessional and extremely uncomfortable—almost like I was being molested rather than receiving a massage. I’ve never felt so uneasy during a session before, and I just wanted it to end as soon as possible.
 
 Extremely disappointing, uncomfortable, and unprofessional. Would not recommend.

title: Coffee Tea Library
text:
Quite disappointed with the experience here. Out of the three visits I have made, I’ve only managed to dine in once despite checking the opening hours prior to the journey over. Found out that this is due to the staff’s break time being unaccounted for within the operational hours listed on their establishment (or Google Maps especially for the first visit - attached picture from first visit on a Saturday, 8/6/24 12PM).
 
 Made my way down with a friend to this place for the swing seats and cozy environment, only to be met by an unforeseen closure of an hour. When asked if we could sit and wait inside until then (as the surrounding area doesn’t have much to do and mosquitoes were flying around), we were turned away as well. I would be understanding if the break was listed like how Korean restaurants choose to take time off in the afternoon, but it’s absolutely disappointing to be turned away for something that is not accounted for within their operating hours stated. Wound up going to a different place instead.
 
 Edit: did not check Google Maps for third visit, but I did ask staff about operational hours during my second visit + checked iG before third visit in case there were any closures not announced on Maps. title: Lite Mobile @ Jurong Gateway
text:
Rating: 1/5 Stars ⭐️
 
 Saw LiteMobile on TikTok FYP for a burn mark on my LCD screen. Went to their branch, got the repair with a "3-month warranty." I pointed out a scratch immediately, but they said it was just dirt! Now there's a bright white spot that wasn't there before! The manufacturer is just rabak!
 
 Their customer service (via WhatsApp) is APPALLING. Instant replies from another's phone pretending to be a new customer, but "bohlayan" when I tried to claim my warranty. After ranting to "Desmond" on WhatsApp, he offered a refund AND a new LCD. I refused because their rabak customer service made me lose all trust. They suddenly claimed my phone had a bloated battery and could damage the screen, wanting to "check" it. Sketchy!
 
 LiteMobile needs to prioritize warranty claims and acknowledge issues instead of dismissing them. First and last time customer here. Save yourself the trouble and go somewhere else!
 
 #Singapore #CustomerServiceFail #TikTokMadeMeTryItAndItFailed #WarrantyNightmare #Rabak #ShadyBusiness

title: Zenith Automotive Services
text: Repair at your own risk. Roy from Zenith Auotmotive appeared to be “Mr Nice Guy” but he is actually a wolf under a sheep skin. Zenith Automotive is managed by Roy, his wife, his son and daughters. I’ve been repairing my car at zenith for more than 5 years. My whole family too as we are all staying nearby. He was introduced to us by our Cycle&Carriage salesperson Han Ai Lin. At first, he appeared to be very nice and honest. But after a few repairs, I felt that something was off. Everytime we repair a problem, a new problem will arise. At first I thought it was pure coincidence but this not only happened to me all the time, but also my dad’s, my mum’s and my sis’s car. The last I remembered was I repaired my aircon at Zenith, 1-2 days after car collection, my engine starts to make weird sounds. His charges seemed to be reasonable like repair for the aircon $800 but in the end I always have to add on another few thousands. This didn’t happen once, it happened many times. This time, I went to repair my new car as my husband has met a small accident. He repaired my bumper for few hundred dollars. He said he repaired the headlamp mounting too. After awhile, our headlights starts to turn misty and the headlights was damaged due to the mist. We went back to Cycle & Carriage and they mentioned that it was because Zenith did not repair it properly, he simply use a glue to repair the mounting, resulting the headlights to have mist and damage it. I have asked a few more workshops and they said the same thing. So his style is to charge a reasonable amount and so you have more new problems and go back and pay more money for the repair. I’ve asked a few workshop friends and realised that he is well-known to be dishonest in the industry. Please do not be fooled by them anymore!!!

title: SkyHelix Sentosa
text:
SkyHelix Sentosa Review: A Decent Experience, But Not for Thrill-Seekers
 
 We visited SkyHelix Sentosa in the morning, hoping for something fun or unique, but left feeling a bit underwhelmed.
 
 The experience involves sitting in a parachute-like open-air gondola that slowly ascends into the sky and gently rotates to offer a 360° view of Sentosa. It lasts about 10-15 minutes. During that time, an instructor gives a short introduction and tries to entertain the group, which was nice, but there’s only so much you can do in that span, especially when the ride itself is very passive.
 
 This is not a ride or anything adventurous. There’s no adrenaline rush, no surprises, just a slow ascent, a calm view, and a slow descent. The view in the morning was okay, but not particularly spectacular. Maybe a sunset or night session would be better for photography or ambiance.
 
 That said, this attraction is suitable for people who aren’t into adventure or thrill rides and are just looking for a mild, scenic experience. It's peaceful and easy, making it ideal for families with young kids or older folks who want a simple, elevated view of the island.
 
 Overall, it’s a decent, short activity, but if you're someone looking for excitement, SkyHelix probably won't deliver that.

title: COURTS Orchard
text:
Staff are not very helpful and not knowledgeable about their products and offerings. Even small 7eleven store cashiers are better than these lazy staff.
 
 I bought a camera here that will be used as a gift. No one was around to help, so I went to the cashier area and asked someone to sell the item to me. I specifically asked if the item I will be buying can be returned as I don't want to open the box since it will be a gift I will give on my overseas trip. The guy who helped me said it could be returned after 14 days. I counted my overseas trip days, and if ever there is a defect, I can still return it after my trip.
 
 Armed with this info, I immediately paid for the item. When I double-checked with the cashier about the return policy, much to my surprise, he said the item only has a 1 week return policy. I argued that they falsely provided sales terms and misled me into buying the item. As a compromise, I asked if they could test it instead, though I am hesitant since I want the box sealed when I give my gift - but to add to the incompetence so far, they said they don't have a dedicated salesperson who can test it.
 
 Since they have no solutions for me and we just stared at each other for minutes with no one offering even a simple apology, much less a work around the issue, I just opted to refund the item.
 
 When the person who will process my refund came and asked the guy if I would need a refund, the guy even had the gall to tell her I changed my mind. I didn't let it pass since they are the one who changed the terms of sale right there, not me. Stores usually get sued and fined for this kind of misleading sales, but the staff are not even bothered by the mistake and incompetence they just displayed. In any other setup, this kind of attitude leads to suspension or even dismissal, but I guess Courts Orchard management is satisfied with being mediocre and incompetent.

title: 60's Hostel
text: Stayed at this hostel for a night between my layover from Hong Kong heading to Malaysia, the reception and kitchen rooms are very small and congested, didn't really appeal to me personally as I prefer a common area and more modern facilities. However, I must say the staff service does get a 5-star rating for me as coming in at 1 am the staff member was SUPER helpful, offering me even some food after travelling late night, very nice service. ||||The dormitory rooms were in a very old style layout and design, it looked more run down to me than old-style but this is more just personal preference, the beds and bunks are a bit hard but for a budget hostel more than fine enough. The showers are a bit weirdly designed in dorms but otherwise, I had no problems staying here with a quick layover personally.

title: The Room @ Bugis
text: Stayed for 4 nights in July 2025. The location is good, just a few minutes walk from Bugis MRT station, and there are many restaurants nearby.However, I give it one star out of five. I don't know about the women's room, but there is only one water tap (sink) for the men's room for over 50 people. There are only four toilets and showers, two separate ones and two in each room. This doesn't seem to violate Singapore law, but it clearly shows the owner's attitude towards his guests. In the morning, you often have to fight with other people over the sink, and it's normal to wait 5-10 minutes. It's not cleaned and dirty.There are also numerous shoes and slippers left in a mess at the entrance, including disposable slippers that have been thrown away. Footwear is not permitted inside the building, but the floors are dirty and indoor beach sandals are a must.There is a refrigerator, but it is not organized at all, and there is rotten food left there, giving off a foul odor, so new guests should assume that it is practically unusable. The price is close to the lowest in the area, so the clientele is extremely poor. The room is small, and there are many suitcases at the entrance, so the door sometimes cannot be opened. There is no space to pack luggage inside the room.

title: Bar Intermezzo
text:
Step into a world where tradition meets indulgence and be impressed with the variety of local flavours at this weekemd only High Tea Buffet at Bar Intermezzo located within Orchard Hotel.
 
 From the fragrant perfection of Signature Singapore Laksa and succulent tenderness of Kong Bak Pau to savoury sweetness of carrot cake and creamy decadence of Durian Pengat, you can enjoy delectable spread of local flavours right here.
 
 We also enjoyed some diy moments at their diy station for Kueh Pie Tee and Rojak. We especially enjoyed their assorted dimsum, chicken curry with Roti Jala and Assorted Nonya Kueh.
 
 Perfect spot for weekend high tea buffet with your loved ones, especially for visitors who are looking to enjoy local flavours at one go in the well-decorated and classy ambience of the bar.
 
 To sweeten the deal, they are having a promo for this high tea buffet at $55++ (U.P. $83++) and comes with a complimentary glass of Prosecco. Available only on weekends for limited time till 31 May 2024 only. So worth it.

I told her this was the only cash I have and she ask me to do Paywave next time, which I also told her that I don't have it at that moment. She proceed to repeat saying I can't do this next time. So many rules for generating one simple receipt, now pay money also need so many rules. You sure its your rules or the 7-eleven rules?! Cause clearly when I go to the other outlets I have never faced such audacity of staff implying rules on their own. Hopes the owner do something about this. From the other reviews I've seen, the previous male Indian staff seems to be an issue as well, time to hire the right employee for a start.

title: Bukit Timah Wet Market & Food Centre (Interim)
text:
The Bukit Timah Temporary Market, set up in October 2024 to house displaced hawkers from the original Bukit Timah Market and Food Centre, continues to deliver on what matters most: food that’s rooted in tradition and flavor.
 
 During a recent visit, the highlight was a plate of Hokkien Mee, which retained the wok hei aroma and balanced seafood richness that fans of the original centre would recognize. The noodles were well-braised, with a generous mix of prawns and squid, and came with a sambal that was both smoky and sharp. Despite the change in location, the quality and character of the dish remain impressively intact.
 
 For dessert, the Ice Kachang offered a refreshing counterpoint. It came tall and finely shaved, with a classic mix of red beans, attap seeds, jelly, and sweet corn, topped with syrup that didn’t overwhelm. The texture and taste were reminiscent of hawker desserts from an earlier era — unpretentious and satisfying.
 
 While the market can feel stuffy, especially during lunchtime, this is an understandable trade-off given its temporary structure and heavy foot traffic. Ventilation fans are in place, but visitors might prefer to come earlier in the day or later in the afternoon for a more comfortable experience.
 
 Despite the spatial limitations, the market maintains a familiar charm. Seating is reasonably ample, the place is kept clean, and stallholders continue to serve food with the same energy and pride as before. For those who frequented the old Bukit Timah Market, the new setup offers continuity — not just in taste, but in spirit.
 
 For anyone looking to revisit old favourites or explore enduring hawker craft, the Jalan Seh Chuan site is well worth the trip.

title: Samsung Electronics
text:
The Most Pathetic Experience with Samsung – Globally and in Singapore
 
 If there were an award for disappointment, Samsung would win hands down. I trusted a globally renowned brand, paid a premium, and ended up with dead pixels on my screen. A quality control issue that has been reported by countless customers worldwide — and yet, Samsung still pretends it’s not a problem.
 
 But wait, it gets worse.
 
 When I reached out to Samsung Singapore’s customer care, hoping for a solution, I was met with a level of indifference that was honestly insulting. Instead of helping, they had the audacity to say:
 “We don’t know how you handled the phone.”
 Seriously? That’s your response? Not only are your devices flawed, but now it’s the customer’s fault for expecting them to work?
 
 I’m baffled. A flagship product with a screen issue and a support team that gaslights the user. This isn’t just bad service — it’s pathetic. For a company that spends millions on marketing and brand image, your actual product quality and support are a disgrace.
 
 To anyone considering a Samsung device: don’t.
 Dead pixels, dead accountability, and dead silence when it comes to real customer issues.

title: Images of Singapore
text:
The Spirit of Singapore Boat Ride at Sentosa's Madame Tussauds is a attractive experience that takes you on a journey through Singapore's rich cultural tapestry. The ride showcases key landmarks and cultural elements by immersive effects and informative narration. The overall enjoyment may depend on personal interest in cultural experiences and educational value rather than thrilling rides.
 
 Images of Singapore is an educational attraction located within Sentosa's Madame Tussauds. Visitors are treated to interactive exhibits, lifelike displays, and multimedia presentations. The attraction is well-curated, providing insights into Singapore. Images of Singapore offers a comprehensive overview in an engaging format.
 
 Some visitors may find it more informative than thrilling. The attention to detail and the quality of presentation make it a valuable experience. It's particularly suitable for families and tourists looking to delve deeper into the local heritage.

Rumour has it that if you stood under this majestic tree from the Alexicus Shelfordae species, you’d be able to smell traces of Nasi Lemak and Truffle for some strange reason. I decided to pay a visit to this tree and lo and behold, the fragrance of Nasi lemak wafted into my nostrils and I fell onto my knees in reverence and started praying.

title: Zion Riverside Food Centre
text: This hawker centre has been around since the 1970s. Set beside the Alexandra Canal, it’s one of the few places to enjoy a meal with a waterfront breeze & city lights. Despite renovations over the years, it has kept its bustling, open-air charm, remaining both a community dining hall & a slice of hawker heritage by the riverside

title: Fort Siloso
text: This historical exhibition facility on Sentosa Island tells the story of wars in Southeast Asia(Especially in Singapore). The explanations are written in three languages: English, Chinese, and Japanese, making it easy to understand. The exhibits are not simply books on the history of the time, but also include photographs, the war situation in each country, and life-size wax figures of wartime meetings. The entire exhibit is packed with information, so we recommend taking your time to explore(at least 2H). It's easy to climb the mountain toward the fort to see the exhibits, and then walk along the Siloso Skywalk on your way back.

title: Bendemeer Market & Food Centre
text: This Hokkieh prawn noodles was good. Forgot to take the stall picture but I reckon there is only one such stall there. Big prawn was succulent & fresh.....noodles taste & soup was good.....stall owner friendly....what more can you ask for 😁

title: Bluewaters Pods 11 North Canal Road
text:
This hostel was unfortunately a letdown. The check-in process was a headache, with gaps in the instructions. Despite reaching out to customer service for help, I still ended up having to figure it out mostly on my own and it took way too long. Self-check-in isn't a new concept, but the way it's handled here is disjointed and leaves a lot to be desired.
 
 Finding the place is next to impossible, and the instructions didn't give the actual location. Like others, I had to rely on reviews to track it down. (PS: If you're struggling to find the entrance, look for a lift inside an unmarked entrance at the back of an alley at a different address — it's at number 13, not 11...)
 
 Once inside, the cleanliness wasn't up to par and trash was scattered around. There's a loud club in the same building that shakes the floor all night. At that point, I decided to cut my losses and found another place to stay.
 
 I appreciated that the staff responded to my concerns by email and we had a polite dialogue, but they refused to provide a refund for future nights I wasn't going to stay. It would have been nice to see more flexibility given the circumstances.
 
 Overall, the experience here wasn't good, and they were content to keep my money despite providing a poor experience. I'd explore other options in the area next time.
 
 Edit: in their public response to my review, the hostel claimed they would be reaching out to me directly to address a concern. I never heard from them.

title: Butternut Tree Hotel
text:
This hotel is absolutely worth recommending, and here’s why:
 
 Location: 3/5
 Cleanliness: 4/5
 Service Attitude: 5/5
 Value for Money: 5/5
 
 I managed to book this hotel at a super affordable promotional rate! To my surprise, the price included a private bathroom — and even room cleaning service, which was unexpected! What impressed me the most was the front desk staff’s service — they were extremely polite and greeted us with a cheerful “Good morning” every day as we left the hotel.
 
 There’s also a bar in the hotel, perfect for relaxing after a long day out. Plus, the hotel provides a public drinking water dispenser — I really appreciated that!
 
 The only downside is that it takes about a 10-minute walk to the nearest MRT station. However, for those who take the bus, the bus stop is very close by. The room isn’t particularly big, but for RM200 a night, I dare you to compare — you won’t easily find another hotel offering a private bathroom and a double bed at this price.
 
 I honestly don’t understand why some people are complaining. If I hadn’t stayed here myself, I might have believed those negative reviews — and almost missed out on this gem!

title: 7-Eleven

text: This is a chicken luncheon and egg wrap. One thing i like about this food is that it is better when it is heated up as you can feel the cheeseness in it and this wrap only cost 3.20 which is to me is a good price for this type of food.

title: Holland Village Market & Food Centre
text: This is a place that has some good restaurants and bars. The vibes are different with other places in Singapore. It is not a tourist area, but more of locals and expatriates gathering place.

title: Bukit Timah Wet Market & Food Centre (Interim)
text: This is a popular hawker centre in the Upper Bukit Timah area - albeit an "Interim" one until its permanent location (just across the road) is ready. This hawker centre retains quite a number of the popular stalls from its previous location - notably the fried carrot cake stall, the satay stall, the thunder tea rice stall to name a few. This hawker centre is sort of divided - that said, unevenly into two, with the smaller section nearer to the Beauty World MRT Station exit. The dining ambience here is better than at the previous location as it is "cleaner" and more spacious.

title: Double Shot Coffee Kampong Bahru
text: This is a really cozy space and clearly, these guys know what they’re doing. I had a phenomenal Quebraditas on filter, and picked up a bag for myself. The baristas are friendly and easy to talk to, they were more than happy to give me some brewing tips. This is a must-visit if you’re into specialty coffee at all.

title: North Bridge Road Market & Food Centre
text: This is a relatively recent refurbishment and is one of the cleanest hawker centers you will come across in Singapore. It is very well ventilated with a few of those long bladed low velocity high volume fans. Next the food… the fish ball noodle shop is open 24hrs … it is excellent. Noodles are al dente and the fish balls are nice. The lor mee is similarly excellent. Can’t say the same about the prawn noodle shop though. It sells prawn noodles, pork rib noodles, wonton noodles, and some combination of chicken and charsiew rice. The noodles are pedestrian and the meats are not very good. The pork rib noodle is tasty but that’s the noodle. The meat itself is not very tasty and not very soft. Ditto the charsiew. Also very strange for pork rib noodles to be served on a plate. It’s just weird. I’d avoid this stall like the plague the next time. I see a very enticing fish porridge soup. Oh and I like the soya bean stall. There are others but not all are open even on a Saturday (or because it is a Saturday… been 3 Saturdays). If visiting, please avoid parking there for Saturday lunch. It took us over 30 mins to get out of the carpark … perhaps because the people going to ICA are parking here and it’s a really bad layout. It felt like waiting in a JB jam. If I crawled, I would have left the carpark in 10 minutes.

title: Frontier Family Medicine Clinic (Clementi)

title: Naughty Girl Club
text: This is by far the WORST bar/club I have been to in Singapore. I got kicked out after spending less than 30 minutes inside. The ridiculous reason given by the rude Indian manager was because I did not purchase another drink after I had finished my first drink. How could he expect me to immediately buy another drink after I had just finished my first drink? His logic was that if I don't buy another drink, I had to leave the club immediately. Out of all the bars/clubs I have been to, this is the only one with the absurd policy whereby customers are expected to immediately purchase more drinks after consuming their previous drinks. The Indian manager had poor customer service and is a horrible jerk. Avoid this place!

title: Coffee Tea Library
text:
This tea cafe is hidden inside the former Salvation Army (which is no longer operating there), which itself is located in a former primary school.
 
 It's very Instagrammable and serves and sells a wide variety of premium specialty coffee beans and tea leaves, including Kopi Luwak (Civet Cat Coffee).
 
 There's a seating area that has hanging swing seats and tables.
 
 No GST or Service Charge.
 
 It's next to the Lucky Saigon Vietnamese restaurant which itself has a forest design with a misty dry ice entrance (powered by fog machines), wooden bridge over a pond => great for romantic dinner dates. There's even a cage with fluffy Vietnamese chicken with giant feet, a food delicacy in Vietnam.
 
 The former school's toilet condition, to be honest, is not great. It's also used by the customers of the gym/ sport businesses elsewhere in the development.
 
 Free open-air carpark. There is a sheltered dropoff point.

title: Butternut Tree Hotel
text:
This was our second time staying at Butternut, and we didn’t even consider looking at other hotels because our first stay left such a positive impression. Most of the staff were still as warm, friendly, and welcoming as we remembered, and we truly appreciated that. However, this recent stay felt quite different from our first.
 
 Previously, we booked the L Room with Queen Bed and Window (12 m²/129 ft²), which felt spacious and comfortable. We had two large suitcases, two small ones, and two personal bags--and we could easily lay both large suitcases open on the floor with slight room to move around. This time, we chose the L Room with Skylight Window, which is also listed as 12 m²/129 ft² on Agoda. However, the layout felt SIGNIFICANTLY more cramped than expected. I cannot stress SIGNIFICANTLY enough. We could only open one suitcase at a time, and with limited floor space, it was difficult to move around...especially after shopping or with larger luggage. The room appeared more spacious in the photos, but in person, it felt closer in size to an M or even an S room. Although the listed area is the same as our previous room, the difference in usable space was quite noticeable, and honestly, it was our biggest letdown during this stay.
 
 We also noticed that some of the amenities listed for our room like slippers, a desk, a telephone, and an in-room or laptop safe were not available. My partner kindly asked the front desk for slippers, but we were told they were unavailable. We're not sure if this was a temporary situation or if these items are no longer part of the standard setup.
 
 Another thing to keep in mind is that there’s no lift access to the 4th floor. You have to take the stairs. This might be important to consider for guests with heavy or bulky luggage and might get a room at the 4th floor. Also, the air conditioning took quite some time (around two hours) to cool the room, which was a bit surprising given its compact size.
 
 We do hope the property stays true to what is described and promised in their listing in the future. We were honestly disappointed by the discrepancies, especially after having such a great first stay last 2023. While we did encounter one staff member who seemed a bit unfriendly, we truly appreciate the rest of the team who were consistently kind, accommodating, and approachable throughout our stay. Their warm hospitality is one of the reasons we might still consider staying at Butternut again...along with its convenient location near Maxwell Food Centre, Maxwell MRT, and Chinatown Complex.

title: Central 24-Hr Clinic (Clementi) - CHAS | GP Clinic | 24 小时 诊所
text:
Truly the worst experience I’ve ever had in a medical setting.
 
 My partner came in in the middle of the night with severe pain on the right side of his body (later discovered, in a much more professional setting, to be a slipped disc). He was in IMMENSE pain, and the counter staff on duty was rude, dismissive, and wouldn’t even get off of her chair to help him like passing him forms. HE was expected to move to her lazy self when he was in so much pain.
 
 Secondly, this place proudly states it’s a 24h clinic, but when we were here, we saw multiple people being turned away because there was no doctor on shift for about an hour in the middle of the night.
 
 My partner has said that every doctor he’s seen here has been fine & helpful, but we experienced EVERY single counter staff member as rude, dismissive, unhelpful and certainly not comforting when you’re already feeling unwell or in pain. Without exaggeration, some of the worst service I’ve ever seen, and definitely the worst of all in any medical setting.

title: Bluewaters Pods 11 North Canal Road
text:
Type: Private Capsule Room
 
 Unfortunately, despite having lived in countless of hostels & hotels daily for a 1 years+, my experience here has been abnormally claustrophobic and noisy. It was certainly not worth staying... (I paid about S$70+ per night for it)
 
 The private room is no different from sleeping in a store room with no windows. The lack of a single light from outside is the same as living in a black hole. Air ventilation is close to none, I had a hard time breathing to which, sleeping in bunk bed would be better.
 
 The worst thing? You can find the room trembling to the loud music from the nightclub above which I remember was way after 1am... Entry into the private room operates by downloading an
 
 They only provide in house showers rooms which are small and lacks space & hook for your clothes + essentials. The building’s toilet outside of the hostel feels super hot located just beside the air duct vacuuming heat from kitchens below.
 
 The large coworking table & local beverage is great. But overall, not worth returning.
 
 Location is great for tourist who wish to visit the Asian Museums and drink alcohol along Boat Quay, Clark Quay etc, and visit the Merlion.

text:
Unethical Business?
 
 My personal experience is that this place feels very iffy because unlike the other TCMs I’ve been to, this one feels very “business oriented”. Went in for a consultation for discomfort in stomach: $40 Consultation, $113 for 1 week medication. Total $153!
 Needless to say I was gobsmacked when I saw the bill.
 
 Also, doctor was pushing for acupuncture right off the bat. Luckily I read some reviews beforehand saying they will try to push services onto you so I declined.
 
 I have been to other TCMs which were very good but never have I seen such pricing. I for one will never visit this place again.
