title: Palace Therapy Spa Massage
text:
Unprofessional and unnecessary remarks of calling Singaporeans calculative and 'one kind', lack of reliability and courtesy.
 
 Called around 11pm to check availability and was told by the counter staff, Jojo, that there was a slot in 15 minutes. I took a cab over, but just few minutes before arriving, she informed me that she had overlooked earlier bookings and that I would now have to wait an hour.
 
 It was close to midnight, and with nowhere else to go, I asked if the cab fare could be reimbursed given the sudden change. Instead, I was met with excuses — that she was new, crossed in and out of JB, had to pay rent, etc. She even went on to say Singaporeans are “calculative,” I told her it's not a matter of being a Singaporean but about professionalism, she insisted that she's right and that she never faced this when working in JB.
 
 She later said that her boss wants to offer discount the next time I visit but with this kind of attitude and still expect me to return there again? No thank you.

title: Palace Therapy Spa Massage
text: Used to be my favorite and reliable spa for late nights. However, my recent experience was not good. Over the phone, I said I needed a 90-minute massage, and the receptionist said OK. When I arrived at the shop, she kept asking if an hour was fine. I had no issue with that, as maybe they wanted to close the shop, but I hoped they had informed me earlier. The massage started nicely, and the masseuse was indeed friendly, but she stopped after 50 minutes. I had to explain to her multiple times, in English, that it should be an hour, and she finally understood. I hope that if the shop wants to close early, they inform customers earlier so that we won't come at all.

title: CompAsia Singapore
text:
Utterly disappointed me for the 3rd time.
 
 I have no choice but to deal with CompAsia because official Samsung engages with CompAsia for their trade-in services. What you see in the screenshot is what happened this year (August 2025), the driver failed to turn up after we have scheduled a pick up of my old phone on the specified date with the reason being "Car Broke Down". The date was arranged almost a month prior. This wasn't a last minute arrangement.
 
 But this wasn't the first time this occured. In the past (2023), when I also traded-in my old phone for a new phone with Samsung, they also used CompAsia for the trade-in service and CompAsia also failed to show up the 1st time with the reason also being "Car Broke Down". We rescheduled to another date then to my shock, they told me they couldn't come again. After I got so mad at them they finally show up on the 3rd reschedule.
 
 So what you see in the screenshot, is what just happened a few days ago (August 2025). Which means this is the 3rd time they failed to show up with the same reason, "Car Broke Down". How bad is the condition of their cars that it keeps breaking down? Everytime CompAsia has to pick up my old phone for trade -in they just couldn't make it. CompAsia doesn't understand that people had to find time and make effort to be at home and wait for them. I took a day off to be home and I'm not being paid for the day I'm not working.
 
 Now they are telling me to reschedule and I have to risk another day of not being paid and them not showing up. They don't do pick-ups on weekends by the way. And they do this to me 3 times. Making the same mistake 3 times just seems intentional.
 
 I don't understand why Samsung is working with them. Samsung definitely needs to know about this especially if I am not the only one experiencing this.
 
 UPDATE : THEY DISAPPOINTED ME THE 4TH TIME
 I've added additional screenshots with numbered sequence so everyone can look at the pictures in order.
 
 1. They said to reschedule to Aug 11th, but I told them I won't be free for at least 2 weeks after they failed to show up on Aug 8th when I was ready to handover the device.
 
 2. They still showed up Aug 11th when I wasn't home. Then tried to blame me for not being home and sent me proof of them being outside my door. But I already told them I won't be home on Aug 11th. They even acknowledged it in email that they are aware I won't be home.
 
 What is wrong with them?

title: RedDoorz Plus Near Gold Coast Ferry Terminal Batam
text:
Very old and tired rooms. BUT the staff, service and location are all great. Big shout out to Alif and Deena. Their service is warm, friendly and professional. Better service than many 4 star hotels.
 
 I also like that each floor (including the lobby / reception area) has large "public spaces" with sofas 🛋️, chairs and coffee tables to lounge at, chill out and grab a snack. That's quite unusual.
 
 You do get the feeling that with some investment, this could be a great little boutique hotel in the Bengkong Laut / Golden City area. The other two hotels (Golden Bay and Golden View) are also pretty old, tired and in desperate need of renovation. Golden View Hotel is also MASSIVELY overpriced.
 
 I'd really like to see this hotel be renovated. The area needs more, good, accommodation because there's a lot to see and do in the area - beaches, beach clubs, historic mosque (Masjid Cheng Hoo), many fantastic eateries, watersports, Wake Park, theme parks, carousel 🎠, 🎡 wheel, food and drink stalls, miniature houses open museum, go kart 🏎️ track etc etc etc.
 
 In Bahasa >
 
 Kamarnya sangat tua dan usang. TAPI staf, layanan, dan lokasinya luar biasa. Salut untuk Alif dan Deena. Layanan mereka hangat, ramah, dan profesional. Layanannya lebih baik daripada kebanyakan hotel bintang 4.
 
 Saya juga suka bahwa setiap lantai (termasuk lobi/area resepsionis) memiliki "ruang publik" yang luas dengan sofa 🛋️, kursi, dan meja kopi untuk bersantai, bersantai, dan menikmati camilan. Hal yang cukup unik.
 
 Anda mungkin merasa bahwa dengan sedikit investasi, ini bisa menjadi hotel butik kecil yang bagus di area Bengkong Laut/Golden City. Dua hotel lainnya (Golden Bay dan Golden View) juga cukup tua, usang, dan sangat membutuhkan renovasi. Golden View Hotel juga SANGAT mahal.
 
 Saya sangat ingin melihat hotel ini direnovasi. Daerah ini butuh lebih banyak akomodasi yang bagus, karena ada banyak hal yang bisa dilihat dan dilakukan di daerah tersebut - pantai, klub pantai, masjid bersejarah (Masjid Cheng Hoo), banyak tempat makan yang fantastis, olahraga air, Wake Park, taman hiburan, komidi putar 🎠, bianglala 🎡, kios makanan dan minuman, rumah miniatur museum terbuka, lintasan go kart 🏎️, dll.

title: COURTS Orchard
text:
Visited Courts Nojima on 3 August to explore buying a dryer. Did not expect it to be the start of many troubles.
 
 Was wrongly advised by sales staff regarding the SG60 discounts ($120 off instead of $60) and use of climate vouchers for a dryer (cannot be used) only at the point of purchase. Decided to proceed with buying the Samsung dryer.
 
 After purchase, did not receive any confirmation of notification of delivery of actual date, only a call 10 mins before delivery. Delivery window was 10am to 2pm, and ended up staying home for 3 hours (10am to 1pm) before getting a call that the delivery was coming. Sales staff also was hard to contact regarding delivery (2 to 3h wait, only responded after calling). Understand it was his off day, but Courts should have a staff to cover for him since it still involved deliveries, or have a more contactable number.
 
 Sales staff also wrongly scheduled the Samsung delivery agent, so ended up the agent only came 1 day after the dryer was delivered. Asked for a specific time for the agent to come (3pm) to make up for the mistake but ended up with delaying my delivery window (originally 2 to 6pm) to 3 to 7pm. As of 545pm, the agent is still not here. (Edit: Agent ended up being late, and I was forced to take cab to my appointment)
 
 This is one of my worst sales service to date, from pre to post sales. The only good things about this whole process was the advice given on the right dryer to buy (pre sales) and the free delivery given in an attempt to recover from the mistake in the supposed discount.
 
 Please work on your service processes and sales recovery. It is alarming how poor the standards are.

title: Jimmy Monkey Cafe & Bar
text:
Visited Jimmy Monkey at PLQ for a casual dinner gathering, as we were looking for a kid-friendly spot.
 
 We were seated at an outdoor table conveniently located right next to the playground, which was great for families with young children. However, do note that the outdoor area had some mosquitoes, so insect repellent might come in handy.
 
 We ordered a variety of dishes to share – the salmon steak, wagyu burger, white clams in white sauce, aglio olio with prawns, cornflake chicken breast, and the sweet & sour cauliflower. They also offer a kids’ menu, which includes a main and drink – a thoughtful touch for families.
 
 Unfortunately, while the food was decent, the service left much to be desired. It appeared that only one service staff was managing the floor, which resulted in a long wait for drinks and multiple reminders needed for cutlery, condiments, and basic requests.
 
 Overall, the experience was underwhelming, and while the location is great for families, we’re unlikely to return given the slow service.

text:

 I was attended to by Jack who was very professional and courteous. He managed to diagnose the problem in a couple of minutes as a blown motherboard fuse and gave me a reasonable and transparent quotation to fix the problem.
 
 3 days later, my iPhone is working as good as a brand new phone again! Jack was also very gracious to add in a free screen protector replacement for me as he had to remove the old one while disassembling my phone. The repair also came with a 3 month warranty. Overall, a 5 star service and I would recommend coming here for phone repair services. Keep up the good work!

title: TUFF CLUB @ Oxley Tower
text:
Visited Tuff Club with two friends on a weekend evening, and unfortunately, this venue falls well short of Singapore's nightlife standards.
 
 Entry & Pricing
 Upon arrival, we were offered two options: $60 standard entry or $80 with bar coupons. We opted for the latter, assuming it would provide better value – a decision we quickly regretted. The coupon system felt like a marketing gimmick rather than genuine added value.
 
 Atmosphere & Crowd
 The venue was surprisingly sparse, with fewer than 30 patrons despite the modest space. Even accounting for the club's compact size, the atmosphere felt lifeless and lacking the energy you'd expect from a proper nightlife venue. The sparse crowd made the evening feel more awkward than intimate.
 
 Interior & Cleanliness
 The bar area desperately needs renovation – the aesthetic can only be described as dated and uninspiring, reminiscent of an old Eastern Bloc establishment. More concerning was the cleanliness standard: our table left black residue on contact, suggesting poor maintenance and hygiene practices. This immediately raised red flags about the venue's upkeep.
 
 Facilities
 The restroom facilities were particularly disappointing – cramped, unclean, and genuinely uncomfortable to use. For a venue charging premium entry prices, basic cleanliness should be non-negotiable.
 Redeeming Features
 The only highlight was the outdoor terrace area, which provided a brief respite from the indoor environment and served as a decent smoking area.
 
 Verdict
 After less than an hour, our group decided to cut our losses and leave. For $80 per person, there are numerous superior venues in Singapore that offer better atmosphere, cleanliness, and overall experience. Tuff Club needs significant improvements in maintenance, crowd management, and basic hygiene standards before it can compete with the city's established nightlife scene.
 Would I return? Definitely not.
 Would I recommend? Only if you're specifically looking for a cautionary tale about Singapore's nightlife scene.

title: The Clinic Group @ Fusionopolis
text:
Visited twice for check up and vaccination. Doctors are efficient. I conveyed my feedback to the anchor Dr Aamir. He promised to speak to the receptionists so hope situation will improve in the future.
 Receptionists have poor understanding of workflow, gave wrong information and still talked down on patients and arrogant.
 1. Enquired on COVID vaccine and RSV vaccine. COVID vaccine needs to register on MOH webpage but NOT the clinic webpage (as advised to scan QR code of clinic at the counter). Only acknowledged this mistake after I offered twice to show them my phone.Told me no RSV vaccine available when it’s shown on website with price. Clearly they don’t even know what vaccine services are provided at the clinic and are too lazy to even look up upon request.
 2. Vaccine record was missed by the first doctor to upload to healthHUB. Could be easily corrected by checking with the doctor. However receptionists first dismissed my request and told me to check with MOH??! Only upon insisting did they register me to clarify with the doctor who admitted it was a missed upload and amended on the spot.
 3. Maid health check up records. We told the receptionists that we need a copy and the receptionists said they’d call us back in about 1 week to collect result. No phone call or follow up. Had to walk in to get result again. Told today that the routine practice is to just upload result to MOM as most customers don’t want a copy?
 All mistakes could have been cordially resolved but the receptionists talking down on patients simply made the experience truly unpleasant.

title: Kang Zu Tang Therapy 康足堂
text:
Visiting a friend in Singapore and was recommended by my local friend to visit Helen姐. Went to see Helen姐 twice during my 4-day trip to Singapore. Waited a week after the treatments to observe the effects before posting a review.
 
 Basically some part of the chronic stiffness I had in my left shoulder and upper back was taken care of. Not that it's totally gone (can't expect that from just two sessions...), but I'd say it was a structural / fundamental kind of change, not just dealing with the surface / symptom level. I've had spine issues for many years and also surgery, and have seen a number of physiotherapists, chiropractors, get massages weekly etc. etc., and I'd say I've not had therapy that's had such a significant change before.
 
 Thank you to Helen姐, and will definitely plan on visiting again in any next Singapore trip.

text:

title: Italian Coffee Lab Singapore
text:
We recently hosted our daughter’s birthday party at this lovely café, and it was a wonderful experience from start to finish. Though it was their first time organizing a private event, café owner Gus went above and beyond to make everything run smoothly.
 
 He thoughtfully suggested that we collect pre-orders for our 60 guests, which really helped his team prepare in advance and serve the food promptly once everyone arrived. He even hired extra staff just for the day to ensure things ran efficiently.
 
 Gus was incredibly accommodating—he allowed the kids (ages 4 and up) to have their own space at the loft, where we held the balloon sculpting and party games. This gave them plenty of room to have fun with minimal restrictions, which we really appreciated.
 
 The food received great feedback from our guests, and everything was served in a timely manner. Special thanks to Bob and Junear as well, who helped a lot with coordination before and during the event.
 
 Highly recommended if you're looking for a cozy, welcoming venue for a private event!

title: Butternut Tree Hotel
text: We recently stayed at this fantastic hotel and it exceeded my expectations in every way! The hotel's central location made it easy to explore the city by being near to Outram and Maxwell MRT. Also, the spotless rooms and corridors impressed me with their impeccable cleanliness. Our room was spacious, comfortable, and was modern-classy decorated with stunning view. We booked the one with balcony. The staff were friendly, attentive, and went above and beyond to ensure my stay was enjoyable, accommodating my requests with ease and providing warm hospitality. Overall, I'd highly recommend this hotel to anyone looking for a comfortable, convenient, and enjoyable stay – it's truly top-notch! Thanks again! 🥰😘

title: The Warehouse Lobby Bar (Robertson Quay)
text:
We visited the Lobby Bar at The Warehouse Hotel on 17 April 2025, and naturally the ambience of the hotel was unparalleled, but the highlight of our evening was Randid. From the moment we arrived, he made us feel welcome and served us delicious passionfruit-infused welcome drinks that had us craving for more.
 
 Randid also took the time to introduce to us some truly unusual spirits, including a memorable mala-infused creation that made me (just me!) want to have Haidilao.
 
 We will be back for more! Thanks again Randid!

title: Luss Restaurant & Bar
text:
We went there yesterday evening for a Valentine's Day dinner, and though it was a last minute reservation, the restaurant staff made sure me and my wife were seated comfortably. They even gifted my wife with roses.
 
 The interior of the restaurant & bar are well-designed & quite newly renovated. Located amongst the lush greenery of nostalgic Portsdown area, we walked through rows of magical flower arches to the restaurant. The atmosphere inside & outside the restaurant was lovely, with alfresco sitting as well; the staff are incredibly friendly and attentive, and the cocktails & food are delicious. Truly a little gem tucked away in the outskirts. Highly recommend!

title: Chang Cheng Mee Wah Coffeeshop
text: We went to one coffeeshop before visiting here. Atmosphere wasn't good, no customers in sight and only a few stalls were opened. We walked some more and located Chang Chern. The place was buzzing with many stalls opened and we were spoiled for. Hoi e. We settled for the zhi Czar stall as the selection were great and met our needs and budget. The the sweet & sour pork ribs didn't disappoint. It was tender and juicy with good aroma and sweet/sour flavour. The bitter gourd with salted egg was just as good. First we try this recipe & found it lightly sauteed with just the right amount of oil. We like this coffeeshope and will definitely go back again.

title: HaveFun Karaoke (Suntec City)
text: We were in full gear from a con event and didn’t feel out of place at all. Staff were super chill, and we sang so many anime openings — the sound system is amazing.

title: Zenith Automotive Services
text: We’ve had a very terrible experience with Zenith, serviced by Roy. We brought the car in and mentioned that there was noise on the front right tyre / suspension and notification on the dashboard that there’s increase in battery discharge when car is stationary even though our battery was changed only 5 months ago. Zenith told us to change front shock absorber and battery. We paid $1,110 for the change. After taking the car back the noise on the tyre was still not resolved, we brought it in and he said he lubricated it so should be ok. But it was not. We brought the car back for the third time and asked to pay another $480 to change something else. We negotiated the price and still paid. 1 month later, the notification on dashboard for battery discharge came up AGAIN. We brought it back in and asked to pay another $200 and they provided the battery life and diagnostics showing another problem. We paid but no idea whether the problem is actually fixed or not.. When I asked him about the battery life and diagnostics on the first visit when we were advised to change the new battery, they gave me a lecture about mutual trust and did not show it (lol). So both our problems when we first brought the car in were not fixed in first visit and we kept going back to check and top up later. Please be careful when dealing with them because you have no idea whether you are paying for the actual fix or not and they don’t seem to do their diagnostics well!

text:
Went on 24 May 2025 for last gaga theme night.
 Made to clear one side of the table as the manager said that we shouldn't occupy the whole standing table. We were placed right at the entrance, 13 of us in total and we open three bottle. Can't even have a full standing table.
 
 After clearing all our drinks to one side, nobody else was using the cleared side table, not even the tables besides us. All were left empty. Since there is nobody using it why is there a need to force all 13 of us to stand to only one side? 3 bottles of gin that we open is still not enough??
 
 Then at around 2a.m, staff were clearing our drinks away from the table already. We werent even finish drinking. When we came back from the dance floor, more than half of our drinks were cleared. It's like they are trying to rush us off. We don't feel welcomed.
 
 I don't recommend going this place. please spend somewhere else. We are the table right at the entrance to the club. Frustrating.

title: THE CHEVRONS Aviary KTV
text:
Went over here few years ago and the service was great back then.
 When I finally came here again after few years with my friend the service were intolerable as when we’ve arrived there were this lady not sure if she was a staff here or a customer however she was very rude.
 After that the waitress here as well given us the feelings that she didn’t want to attend to us.
 We ordered our foods and drink and the other two staff were much better.
 After that we asked what time is the last order they told us it’s 11:30pm however at 11:12pm they came over and ask for last order.
 I’m not demanding and I tried to understand that they also want to go home earlier.
 So I ordered my last order.
 I ordered 2 items and I suddenly felt that I wanted to order 1 more so I went to find the waitress at the counter to asked if I could add on.
 She told me I couldn’t order anymore and the item already well prepared.
 What I see was only a bucket of beer but what about my food that I ordered.
 I asked her and she insisted that I only ordered the bucket of beer whereby she already acknowledged when I ordered.
 Ended up she asked another colleague to come over and well I told her what happened and she also answered me in a way there’s nothing she could do as they are closing soon whereby it’s only 1125pm at that time.
 I have never had any experienced in any other places.
 Such a rude staff & irresponsible staff.
 Highly not recommended.
 To be fair the food was nicely prepared and delicious but what I could not tolerate was the service here.

title: Riverview Auto Services Pte Ltd
text:

I've went to the cheapest car workshops to service my car before but it cannot be compared to Riverview Auto. I also think it's better to do a good one for my six year old car rather than going to a cheaper but lousy alternative.
 
 It was worth the money. Not only were they friendly and helpful when I was in doubt, the boss recommended what work was needed to be done for my car. There were many parts that needed to be changed that the previous workshops didn't tell me to.
 
 After servicing, my car ride was smoother. My car didn't vibrate so much anymore and my steering wheel was so smooth like butter. It was as if my car is brand new.
 
 Highly recommend their car servicing!

title: Central 24-Hr Clinic (Clementi) - CHAS | GP Clinic | 24 小时 诊所

To my horror, the consult was less than 1 minute long. Went into treatment room and was asked about my condition. After sharing, was told" ok u can wait outside". No explanation or any concerns to my conditions at all. While waiting for medication and bill, 5 numbers after me was called. Just imagine the 5 patient going in and out of the tretament room in less than 10 mins. For the duration of the consult and the unprofessional attitude given by the doctor, its should be $10 instead. Receptionist was monotoned and looks like walking dead. No expression and not professional at all. If not in the mood to work (doctor/recptionist), just go home. Dont waste everyones time. Total bill went up to $172.😱😱 Overall, dont even deserve a star for such service. Even polyclinic could do better.

title: Queenstown Polyclinic
text: Zero if I could. It is stated clearly on the website that we can walk in for our flu vaccination. I arrived at 2:50pm to walk in with my sister who had an appointment for flu vaccination. The counter staff was rude and insist that I cannot walk in for flu vaccination even when I told her the website clearly stated that we could. She denied and cut me off rudely with a “June 4th is your earliest appointment date”. Keep insisting the system say cannot. However, my sister ask the nurse and she say that usually walk in appointments are allowed. My family members usually walk in for flu vaccinations and there’s no issue. There’s clearly an inconsistency between your staff and what is stated on the website. This speaks volume and shows the need for you to retrain your staff.

title: Samsung Service Centre Westgate
text:
Zero stars.. This is hands down one of the most frustrating and painful service experiences I’ve had. I brought in a Samsung device for what should have been a straightforward power button repair. I was first quoted around $200, then later received a text saying that the cost had increased to over $400—with no proper explanation.
 
 When I finally received a call, I was told the technician had now found the touchscreen to be “faulty.” How convenient—this issue only appeared after they disassembled the device. I was then told they couldn’t perform a partial repair just for the power button, so I’d have to pay for the screen as well.
 
 Over the phone, I specifically asked multiple times if my device would be returned in the same condition if I didn’t proceed and the person acknowledged that it would, and I made my expectations very clear. Even before sending it in, I made this expectation known—but now, of course, no one will admit to it.
 
 When I didn’t proceed with the repair and came to collect my device, I checked and had to ask them to charge and demonstrate it—and that’s when it was revealed the screen wasn’t even showing the charging indicator anymore.
 
 Here’s the worst part—when they tried to justify it, they told me that fixing the button would “unavoidably” damage the touchscreen, meaning I’d be forced to pay for both. If that was the case, WHY wasn’t it disclosed upfront? Why quote one thing, then hold my device hostage with unexpected, unexplained charges?
 
 Zero transparency. No accountability. The responses felt scripted, and the way things were handled left me, the customer, feeling like I was somehow at fault for not asking the “right” questions—when I had, multiple times. Save yourself the trouble. Don’t send your device here unless you’re ready to be overcharged, misled, and left angry and helpless.

text:

 2段ベッド上の部屋でしたがハシゴの幅が少し大きかったかもしれません。
 シャワーとトイレ同じになっているのでシャワーを使った後のトイレに入るとトイレがびちゃびちゃです。海外ならあるあるですが日本人の方は不慣れな形式なので戸惑うかもしれません。
 洗濯乾燥機が3台、ドライヤー2台、アイロンとアイロン台が1台づつ、ウォーターサーバー、冷凍冷蔵庫、WiFiもあり充実していました。
 WiFiは夜22:00~0:00頃は使用者が多いのか速度がかなり遅くなりました。
 周りは夕方から夜中まで活気のあるレストランが多かったので深夜にお腹が空いたら重宝しましたが夜中に酔っ払いの声が聞こえてきたりもします。

title: The Warehouse Lobby Bar (Robertson Quay)
text:
🌿⬛️ The Warehouse Lobby Bar
 🟧 The Warehouse Hotel
 320 Havelock Road
 Singapore 169628
 
 🟫 The Warehouse Lobby Bar at the Warehouse Hotel at Havelock Road is a stylish and industrial-chic bar that serves up craft cocktails in a unique and atmospheric setting.
 
 🟧The lobby bar is situated in a beautifully restored 19th-century warehouse (built in 1895), with exposed brick walls, high ceilings, and polished concrete floors. The decor is modern and sleek, with comfortable & plush sofa seating areas and a lively bar counter.
 
 🔵 The drink menu is creative and extensive, with a focus on handcrafted cocktails. The bar also serves a selection of wine, beer, and champagne.
 
 🟨 We ordered 2 cups of Hot Cafe Latte and were served by Isabelle, a very polite, nice and cheerful lady.🩷 Because of Isabelle's great & empathetic attitude, I am giving the Warehouse Lobby Bar 5 stars.
 
 ⬛️ Overall, the Warehouse Lobby Bar is a great spot to relax and unwind with friends or family, and take in the stylish and historic surroundings.
 
 🌿🔵 Dated 15th Feb 2025 Sat at approx 8pm.

title: Pancur Larangan
text:
🌿Pancur Larangan is a water themed Garden set in a traditional Javanese style landscape with an intricately crafted beautiful wall mural feature depicting life in the Fort Canning Park from 1300s to 1800s.
 🦋Visitors are immediately drawn to the soft flowing water and it's beautiful surrounding landscape.
 The entire place feels soothing and has a calming effect.
 🍈It let you slow down, soaking in the embience and enjoy the moment of peace and tranquility.
 Fun fact:
 🫚Pancur Larangan or "Forbidden Spring" was a bath place for the noble ladies of the royal court of Singapura during ancient time.
 A spring used to flow from the west side of the hill.

title: Alexandra Arch Overhead Bridge
text:
🌿🌳 My husband, myself and friends had been here to Alexandra Arch a few times over the years to hike and walk here for exercise purposes.
 
 🟢☘️🌾 The view from the Treetop Walk ( after Alexandra Arch) is full of scenic verdant green landscapes. It is really a very beautiful treetop walk.
 
 ✳️🟨 I would like to encourage people from all walks of life to come here to walk, stroll, and take in the beauty from the walks.

title: CS Fresh Great World
text:
🎁SG souvenir choice🎁
 GreatWorldモール地下１階にあるスーパー
 比較的大きく品揃えが豊富なので、大概の物は手に入る。
 
 また、シンガポールブランドのお茶やコーヒー、シンガポール発じゃないけど、お土産にオススメなグラノーラやミックスナッツ等、お土産探し目的でもいろいろある。
 
 奥のワインセクションにいくとインドネシアのコーヒーチェーン tanamera coffeeのカウンターがあり、カップでの注文はもちろん、コーヒー豆も購入可能だ。
 
 お支払は有人レジよりも、セルフレジ方が数が多いのでそっちで精算する方が早い。
 
 <トイレ>
 モール内のトイレを利用しましょう。

title: FUTURA BOUTIQUE HOSTEL
text:
👍Letto comodissimo, struttura nuova e ben curata, disponibili 2 lavatrici e 2 asciugatrici ad uso gratuito, frigorifero, aria condizionata nella camera, 10 minuti a piedi da 2 fermate della metro, fermata autobus di fronte l'ingresso.
 👎Forse il rapporto tra bagni e docce disponibili in funzione del numero di posti letto, non era ottimale.
 Inoltre bisognerebbe prevedere un minimo di areazione delle camere essendo sprovviste di finestre.

title: Faber Point
text:
📸Faber Point, at one of the highest point in Mount Faber offers stunning panoramic views.
 🌳🌿A large tree with wide spread canopy and other surrounding lush vegetations provide much needed shade to the entire place.
 🖼️Below the spacious lookout deck are a series of artistic wall murals depicting the Singapore Stories.
 🦁Nearby, is a mini version of the iconic Merlion.
 📽️Faber Point is one of the checklist for any visit to Mount Faber Park.

title: Jimmy Monkey Cafe & Bar
text:
🟧 Jimmy Monkey Cafe & Bar
 ✳️ Unit 01-51, One-North Residences,
 9 One-north Gateway, Singapore 138643
 
 🟢 Nestled away in the verdant & lush vicinity of One-North Residences, Jimmy Monkey Cafe is a hidden gem delight that blends laid-back charm with a casual cafe culture vibe.
 
 🟦 The cafe is situated at the foot of a block of low-rise condominium residences.
 
 ✳️ This small cafe offers a tranquil escape that feels far removed from the city’s buzz—yet it remains accessible.✔️ The cafe is just a short walk from One-North MRT station.
 
 ⚫️ The decor is industrial-chic style — think exposed brick, polished concrete, and warm wood tones offset by eclectic vintage accents.
 
 🔵 Service here is friendly & casual. The staff here strikes a fine balance between pleasant hospitality and efficient operation.
 
 🟠 The cafe latte here is smooth and rich with a full-bodied espresso base—clearly well crafted. ▪︎ Coffee is served from an exclusive hand-crafted Slayer Machine.
 
 🟫 The grilled cheese sandwich was hearty and satisfying, served warm with just the right crunch. It’s comfort food done well.
 
 🟨 The scone had a rustic homemade quality—great with a pat of butter & jam and a sip of that good coffee. My hubby and I shared the food.
 
 🔷️ On weekdays, this is a serene space that invites you to slow down, relax, and enjoy the moment. It's quiet here and I've been here several times over the years since 2013, because one of my cousins lives in this area.

title: Giant Supermarket
text:
🟩 This is the Giant Supermarket behind our Blk 27 Toa Payoh East.
 
 🟦 This Giant supermarket is situated below a Multi-storey carpark complex at Blk 260, Kim Keat Ave, Toa Payoh East area.
 
 🟧 This is our basic go-to supermarket. I usually get my Meiji coffee milk bottles here and other essentials like sugar, kitchen towel paper, toilet paper rolls, etc.
 
 ❇️ This Giant supermarket is a medium-sized one. ✅️ This supermarket stocks the basic essential items the residents here need.

title: Blind Massage Services
text: 구글 맵 보고 맹인 마사지샵 후기가 좋아서 일부러 멀리 찾아왔습니다 너무너무 친절하시고 깔끔해요. 마사지사분들은 총 세 분 계시고 사전 예약 안하고 워크인으로 방문했습니다. 라벤더역에서 내려서 약 12-15분 정도 걸은거 같아요. 초행길이라서 좀 헤맸는데 가게들 다양히 모여있는 상가의 2층에 있으니 저처럼 1층에서 헤매지 마세요. 며칠전에 다른 마사지샵에서 목 어깨 받고 너무 실망했는데 여긴 제대롭니다. 엄지로 마사지 강력하게 해주시네요. 보통 맹인 마사지사분들이 실력이 전문가시라 믿고 왔는데 첫날부터 올걸 그랬어요.. 내일 새벽에 돌아가는데 ..너무 아쉽네요. 다음에 싱가포르 올때 꼭 다시 올겁니다. 한국분들이 잘 모르시는 로컬샵인 것 같아서 후기 남깁니다. 아 참, 현금만 되니 꼭 현금 챙겨오세요~!!

title: SkyHelix Sentosa
text: 센토사섬에 도착했는데 근처 전망을 보고 싶어서 스카이헬릭스를 탔습니다. 케이블카를 탈까 스카이헬릭스를 탈까 고민을 많이 했었는데 스카이헬릭스가 더 나은 선택이었습니다. 케이블카는 그냥 이동하면서 경치 구경하는게 끝이지만 스카이헬릭스는 15분 정도 상공에서 체류하면서 근처 경치를 계속 볼 수 있는 게 장점이었습니다. 그리고 기구 운영하는 직원이랑 이런 저런 이야기도 하고 그 분이 사진도 찍어주셔서 좋았습니다. Isqandar 직원분이 친절하게 사진도 찍어주고 이런 저런 이야기를 해줘서 고마웠습니다! 그리고 매표소에는 한 사람에 20달러라고 적혀 있었는데 막상 결제하니까 한 사람에 15달러였습니다. 왜 가격이 더 저렴한지는 모르겠습니다만 15달러 주고 탔습니다. 개인적으로는 케이블카보다 가성비 있었네요. 감사합니다!

title: Fragrance Hotel - Rose
text:
아내와 어린 딸과 함께 투숙
 짧은 여행일정으로 잠만 자려고 선택함
 1일간 창문없는 방과 창문 있는 방에 하루 씩 투숙함
 
 창문없는 방(2층)은 낡고 에어콘, 욕실 배수관 소음이 심했음.
 바닥도 끈적임이 있었음.
 침구는 깨끗해 보였고, 벌레가 없어서 괜찮음
 
 창문 있는 방(5층)은 전날 묶었던 방보다 살짝 작지만 창문이 있어서 좋았음
 역시 침구는 깨끗했음. 에어콘과 욕실 배수관 소음은 조금 덜했음
 
 두곳 모두 냉장고가 없으며, 프런트에 문의해보니 아이스버킷도 없음.
 커피와 차는 티백으로 있음.
 
 프런트 직원 분들은 밝고 친절했음.
 
 정류장과 Shaw Plaza(Mall)이 멀지 않음.
 
 숙소에 머무는 시간이 많지 않은 여행객에게는 적합하다고 생각함.

text:

title: Snooze Inn @Dunlop Street
text:
値段以下こんな酷いレベルのホテルに泊まったのは初めて
 ドミトリールームに宿泊
 部屋に窓はなく 天井も低いのでかなり圧迫感があった
 特にトイレ＆シャワーは異常なほど汚い。ハエは飛んでるわ変な匂いするわで最悪でした
 ベットも汚くダニなのかトコジラミがいるのか横になった瞬間身体中が痒く寝られませんでした
 また、インド系人が殆どで夜や朝から部屋で大声で電話したり、音楽流したりしてマナーがなってない
 いびきもうるさいわで全く落ちつかなかったです
 ただ、駅近で立地が良かったのとホテルの人の愛想は良かった

title: Ji Yue Coffee (集月咖啡)
text:
初の来店でした。店内は狭いので3人ぐらいしか座れませんが、天井が高く、居心地の良いカフェです。店内に入れなかった人はテイクアウトして、このカフェが入ってる小さなショッピングセンターの前にあるシーティングエリアで飲んでるみたい。店内は色調が落ち着いてるし、程良いノスタルジアがたまらない。超オススメ。Pasir Panjang に来たら、今後は立ち寄ることにしよう❣️オーナーの若いご夫婦も人柄が良いです。コーヒーも美味しい。自分好みの酸味が薄ら感じられるタイプのコーヒー❣️
 
 ***********
 去年暮れにスペース拡張して、座席増えました。居心地の良さは変わらず。センスが良いです。オーナーご夫婦が旅行中に撮った写真や気に入って買ってきたアートが飾られてます。あと静かな時間を好む大人が集まってきてるように思います。商業的なカフェにありがちな、チャラチャラした声がしないのは有り難い。

title: UDON DON BAR
text:
利用桌上QRcode點餐，等到號碼機叫到我的號碼後過去拿餐，結果服務員把我推開跟我說等到我叫到你在來拿，然後過了一分鐘後又跑過來跟我說我的餐被他拿給其他客人吃掉了😅
 最後問我能不能接受另一組客人點的餐點，所以最後我被逼迫接受一個10塊的辣味拉麵（我原本點的是13塊的牛肉烏冬），反正叫號的人操作相當逆天需要多加小心，以免自己的餐點被他拿去給其他人吃掉了，重點他也沒退我錢，就多給了我一個1塊的蛋
 並且叫號的人明顯有精神問題，他會瘋狂按叫號機直接你來拿餐點，每個號碼都要聽他至少按五次的叫號機，吃個午餐一直聽到他在那叮叮叮叮真的快煩死了

text: 我是朋友推荐来这里找xiang xiang按摩的，说她的按摩手法和力道真的很好，因为我本身经常都肩膀酸痛…甚至睡觉都睡不好，所以我就好奇的心态来这里找xiang xiang帮我按摩，不得不说 她的手法和力道真的非常好👍🏻真需要给个赞👍🏻 主要是酸痛的部位真的没那么痛了 如果你们也有我同样的身体酸痛的话 真值得推荐大家来找她帮你按摩 服务也非常好 我下次一定会回来找她。

title: FM FoodMaster
text: 我觉得我一定要评论Aperia Foodcourt最里面的那家菜饭档口。新装修开张后，我从上个星期就打算来光顾这家菜饭档口，因为种类很多看着很美味😋所以我今天就满心期待的来打包我的午餐。因为队伍很长，菜色也很多，一眼是看不完的。在这么多的选择下，你只要多想2秒，店员就把手里的饭甩掉，丢在一个角落然后人转身就走，一句话都没说。这让我深刻体验到极差的服务态度，我知道或许你煮菜要煮很热很累，但是我真心觉得如果你是这种态度你还是在厨房里面呆着就好。😓美好的午餐心情，多少有被那位大叔给影响了。想唱那首菜饭歌了。。。

title: Tiong Bahru Market
text:
新加坡中峇魯市場是來SG這幾次，最乾淨的市場。
 
 一樓是一般市場，二樓是熟食中心，選擇非常多，胃只有一個，所以買了排隊最多的燒肉與蝦麵。
 
 燒肉皮脆肉嫩，不愧是新加坡十大燒臘之一；蘇東蝦麵分3、4、5塊三種價位，一般食量的人吃3塊的就好囉！
 #新加坡旅遊 #新加坡美食 #新加坡美食 #中峇魯市場 #中峇魯美食 #新加坡燒臘 #蘇東蝦麵

Very bad attitude. I don't know how the 4.9 rating came by itself. Everybody don't go. Go once and regret it.

title: FUTURA BOUTIQUE HOSTEL
text:
距离旅游景点偏远，步行至地铁站要10分钟，不提供早餐。但是靠近老居民区，附近有一家本地食阁，种类多价格便宜，这里更适合长期居住。
 
 二楼公共区域很大，可以办公看书和免费洗衣服但是要自己买洗衣粉。多人房间相对狭窄，大行李箱摊开几乎没法走路，但是床单干净整洁，接待印度小哥人很好。
 
 最后要吐槽办理入住！！！机器刷护照自助入住，下午3点以后才能操作——相当于3点前我只能拿着行李在门口干等着，不能进屋不能寄存行李，非常的不方便！！！门口也没人接待，最后是其他房客出门，打开门才进的屋。

text:
金曜～月曜まで3泊しました。口コミを見てコスパが良さそうと思いましたが、防音が皆無なのでそこだけは注意が必要です。部屋によると思いますが、202の部屋(エントランス側)だと窓が全開になっているのではないかと疑うほど、外の音が全て入ってきます。
 
 深夜3時まで外は音楽がガンガン(日曜の夜でさえ)、人のしゃべっている内容まで聞こえる、工事音やバイクのエンジン音のうるささは、まるで外で布団を敷いて寝ているかのようなレベルです。
 
 また、3日間の滞在中、タオルはリクエストすれば新しいものがもらえますが、夜になるとスタッフが不在になるので、朝一に依頼することをおすすめします。
 
 ホテル自体や立地を考えるとシンガポールの中ではコスパがいい方なのだと思いますが、耳栓や完全防音のヘッドホンをしなければ本当に寝れません。おかげでこの3日間寝不足になりました。もし次泊まるとしたら窓無しの部屋を選びます。こんなにもうるさいのであれば、そもそも窓がない部屋の方がマシな気がします。ただ、寝不足になるくらいなら追加でお金を払ってでも、部屋の中にいると思えるホテルに泊まります。

title: b88 hostel
text:
非常的推薦B88 Hostel.他是我在新加坡住過最好的青年旅館.
 目前為止待過性價比最高的Hostel.原因如下:
 1. 價格真的很便宜
 2. 床鋪很乾淨,連續住兩天 可以發現他們都有換洗枕頭套及被單.
 3. 服務人員很親切,尤其是佩穎,連續兩天帶我去體驗新加坡生活,儘管我之後搬到其他青年旅舍.
 4. 地點位置佳,離小印度及阿拉伯街都很近.雖然離地鐵站有10分鐘的距離.
 
 整體來說,在房間裡面有自己的空間(類似膠囊房),公共客廳又很有家庭的感覺.大家會在那邊看電視聊天.
 
 非常推薦 ,值得一住
 
 Scott Ho 2013.3.4 From Taiwan
